e Story of England's 1966 World Cup Triumph\n| year = 2006\n| origyear=1995\n| location=London\n| publisher =Mainstream Publishing\n| isbn = 978-1-78057-322-9\n| ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Lawton\n| first = James\n| title = Nobby Stiles: After The Ball\n| year = 2003\n| location=London\n| publisher =Hodder & Stoughton\n| isbn = 978-0-340-82887-8\n| ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=Sir Alf: A Major Reappraisal of the Life and Times of England's Greatest Football Manager\n|first=Leo\n|last=McKinstry\n|authorlink=Leo McKinstry\n|year=2010\n|origyear=2006\n|publisher=HarperSport\n|location=London\n|isbn=978-0-00-719379-0\n|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book\n| last = Ramsey\n| first = Alf\n| title = Talking Football\n| year = 1952\n| edition =First\n| location=London\n| publisher =Stanley Paul\n| oclc=9136896\n| ref= harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Alf Ramsey}}\n{{wikiquote|Alf Ramsey}}\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n* {{Englandstats|780|Alf Ramsey}}\n* [http://englandfootballonline.com/TeamPlyrsBios/PlayersR/BioRamseyAE.html Alf Ramsey] at England Football Online\n* {{soccerbase (manager)|57|Alf Ramsey}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = England squads\n| bg = white\n| fg = #0B0B3F\n| bordercolor = #0B0B3F\n| list1 =\n{{England squad 1950 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{England squad 1966 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{England squad UEFA Euro 1968}}\n{{England squad 1970 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Awards\n|fg=navy\n|bg=gold\n|list1=\n{{Football League 100 Legends}}\n{{FIFA World Cup winning managers}}\n{{English Football Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Managerial positions\n| list1 =\n{{Ipswich Town F.C. managers}}\n{{England national football team managers}}\n{{Birmingham City F.C. managers}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ramsey, Alf}}\n[[Category:1920 births]]\n[[Category:1999 deaths]]\n[[Category:1950 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:1966 FIFA World Cup managers]]\n[[Category:1970 FIFA World Cup managers]]\n[[Cat