mer in a Variety Show || {{NA}} || {{Won}} ||<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\uac15\ud638\ub3d9 \ub300\uc0c1-\uc774\uc2b9\uae30 2\uad00\uc655, \uace8\uace0\ub8e8 \ud2b8\ub85c\ud53c \ud488\uc548\uc5d0|trans-title= '2010 SBS Entertainment Grand Prize' |author=Lee Jung-ah|language=ko|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2010/12/31/2010123100069.html|work=Chosun|accessdate=September 16, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2011 || Honorary Ambassador for Youth 2011|| {{NA}} || {{NA}} || {{Won}} ||<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:[\uc0ac\uc9c4]\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, '\uccad\uc18c\ub144 \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \uae30\ubed0\uc694'|trans-title=Minho named Honorary Ambassador for Youth 2011|quote=Shinee's Minho, appointed as the honorary ambassador for Youth 2011, is receiving a name plate at the Youth Week celebration held in the COEX auditorium on May 23, 2011.|language=ko|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2011/05/23/2011052301383.html|work=Chosun|accessdate=September 16, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2012 || rowspan=\"2\"| [[2012 SBS Drama Awards|SBS Drama Awards]] || New Star Award || rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[To the Beautiful You]]'' || {{Won}} || rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{cite web|title=[SBS\uc5f0\uae30\ub300\uc0c1]\ub274\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc0c1, \uc544\uc774\ub3cc\uc2a4\ud0c0\ub9cc 4\uba85 \uc218\uc0c1|language=ko|url=http://news.joins.com/article/10310139|work=JoongAng Ilbo|accessdate=December 23, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827172646/http://news.joins.com/article/10310139|archive-date=August 27, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Couple Award (with [[Sulli]]) || {{Won}} \n|-\n| 2013 || [[2013 MBC Drama Awards|MBC Drama Awards]] || Best New Actor || rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Medical Top Team]]'' || {{Nominated}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=MBC\uc5f0\uae30\ub300\uc0c1 \u7537\uc2e0\uc778\uc0c1 \ud6c4\ubcf4, \ubc15\uc11c\uc900 \uc624\ucc3d\uc11d \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 \ub4f1 \ud655\uc815|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20131226n11304|work=Nate|accessdate=December 27, 2013|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2014 || [[Baeksang Arts Awards]] || Most Popular Actor (TV) || {{nom}} ||<ref>{{cite news | language=ko | url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/100sang |work=JoongAng Ilbo| title=Baeksang Award, Most Popular Male Actor | date=April 28, 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n|  rowspan=\"1\"|[[MBC Entertainment Awards]] || rowspan=\"1\"| Popularity Award (Music Talk Show) || rowspan= \"1\" | ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' || rowspan=\"1\" {{won}} || <ref>{{cite news | language=ko | url=http://joynews.inews24.com/php/news_view.php?g_menu=700100&g_serial=873498 |work=Joy News | title=[MBC \uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1]\uc720\uc7ac\uc11d \ub300\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1\u2026'\uc9c4\uc9dc\uc0ac\ub098\uc774' 9\uad00\uc655(\uc885\ud569)| date=December 12, 2014|accessdate=August 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | language=ko | url=http://news.joins.com/article/19326372 | work=JoongAng Ilbo | title='\uc74c\uc911' \uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638 \uc778\uae30\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1 \"\uadf8\ub140\uc11d \ud615\uc5d0\uac8c\ub3c4 \uace0\ub9d9\ub2e4\"[MBC\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c12015] | date=December 29, 2015 | accessdate=August 27, 2016 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827084926/http://news.joins.com/article/19326372 | archivedate=August 27, 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2017 || Indonesian Television Awards || Special Award || {{NA}} || {{won}} ||<ref name=\"special award\">{{cite news | url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110736471 |work=JoongAng Ilbo| script-title=ko:\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, \uc778\ub3c4\ub124\uc2dc\uc548 \uc2dc\uc0c1\uc2dd\uc11c \uc218\uc0c1..\"\u97d3\uac00\uc218 \uc911 \uc720\uc77c\"|trans-title=SHINee's Minho Receives Special Award At Indonesian Television Awards 2017|author=Lee So-dam|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170921165527/http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110736471|archivedate=September 21, 2017| date=September 21, 2017 | language=ko }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[54th Grand Bell Awards]]|| Best New Actor|| ''[[Derailed (2016 film)|Derailed]]'' || {{nom}} ||<ref>{{cite news | url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000597219&spi_ref=m_entertain_twitter |work=Naver| script-title=ko:\uc81c54\ud68c \ub300\uc885\uc0c1\uc601\ud654\uc81c \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc791 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026'\ub354 \ud0b9'\ubd80\ud130 '\ud0dd\uc2dc\uc6b4\uc804\uc0ac'\uae4c\uc9c0 |trans-title=Nominees for the 54th Grand Bell Awards revealed | date=September 29, 2017|author= Jo Youkyung | language=ko }}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|3rd [[Asia Artist Awards]]\n|Asia Brilliant Award\n|{{NA}}\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/11/28/bts-win-the-daesang-at-asia-artist-awards-2018-and-are-among-artists-of-the-year-8187121/|title=BTS win the Daesang at Asia Artist Awards 2018 \u2013 and are among Artists Of The Year|date=November 28, 2018|website=Metro}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Shinee discography]]\n*[[List of awards and nominations received by Shinee]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://shinee.smtown.com Shinee Official website]\n\n{{Shinee}}\n{{SM Entertainment}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Choi, Min-ho}}\n[[Category:Shinee members]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male rappers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television presenters]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean male actors]]\n[[Category:Konkuk University alumni]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Incheon]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{other people}}\n{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Korean name|Choi}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                 = Choi Min-ho\n| image                = 190106 \ubbfc\ud638 - 33rd Golden Disc Awards 02.jpg\n| image_size           =\n| caption              = Minho at the 33rd Golden Disc Awards in 2019\n| native_name          = \ucd5c\ubbfc\ud638\n| birth_name           = \n| birth_date           = {{birth date and age|1991|12|09}}\n| birth_place          = [[Incheon]], South Korea\n| occupation           = {{hlist|Singer|actor|songwriter|rapper}}\n| father               = [[Choi Yun-kyum]]\n| website              = \n| module               = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background           = solo_singer\n| genre                = [[K-pop]]\n| instrument           = Vocals\n| years_active         = 2008\u2013present\n| label                = [[SM Entertainment|SM]]\n| associated_acts      = {{hlist|[[Shinee]]|[[SM Town]]}}}}\n| module2 ={{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| hangul = {{linktext|\ucd5c|\ubbfc|\ud638}}\n| hanja  = {{linktext|\u5d14|\u73c9|\u8c6a}}\n| rr     = Choe Min-ho\n| mr    = Ch'oe Minho\n}}\n|signature = Choi Minho signature.png\n| alias                = \n}}\n\n'''Choi Min-ho''' ({{Korean|hangul=\ucd5c\ubbfc\ud638}}; born December 9, 1991<ref name=\"Russell2014\">{{cite book|first=Mark | last=Russell|title=K-Pop Now!: The Korean Music Revolution|page=67|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=etDZAwAAQBAJ|date=April 29, 2014|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|isbn=978-1-4629-1411-1}}</ref>), better known by the [[mononym]] '''Minho''', is a South Korean singer, actor, songwriter and rapper . He debuted as a member of South Korean [[boy group]] [[Shinee]] in May 2008 who later went on to become one of the best-selling artists in Korea.  Aside from group activities as singer, he has debuted as an actor in November 2010 in a [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS2]]'s drama special, entitled ''[[Pianist (Drama special)|Pianist]]''.<ref name=\"Minho debut acting\"/> He has since had roles in various television dramas such as [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]' sitcom, ''[[Salamander Guru and The Shadows]]'' (2012), ''[[To the Beautiful You]]'' (2012), ''[[Medical Top Team]]'' (2013), ''[[My First Time (TV series)|My First Time]]'' (2015) and ''[[Hwarang: The Poet Warrior Youth]]'' (2016). He made his feature film debut in 2016 with ''[[Canola (film)|Canola]]''.\n\n==Career==\n===2008\u201309: Career beginnings and Shinee===\n{{Main|Shinee}}\nMinho was discovered at the SM Casting System in 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20080529/8583787/1|script-title=ko:5\uc778\uc870 \ud2f4\uc5d0\uc774\uc800\uadf8\ub8f9 '\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8', \uc2e4\ub825&\ud48b\ud48b\ud568\u2026\"\ub204\ub098\ub4e4\uc774 \uc608\ubed0\ud574\uc694\" |work=Donga|accessdate=January 19, 2009|date=May 29, 2008|language=ko|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160726214055/http://news.donga.com/3/all/20080529/8583787/1|archivedate=July 26, 2016|first=Hong | last=Jae-hyun}}</ref> and modeled for Ha Sang-beg's Seoul Collection F/W 08\u201309 in March 2008.<ref>{{in lang|ko}}[http://news.nate.com/view/20100708n04225 \ubbfc\ud638\ub9de\uc544? \ud30c\uaca9 \ubcc0\uc2e0 \uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ud2f0\uc800 \uc0ac\uc9c4 \uacf5\uac1c] ''Nate''. Retrieved December 15, 2010.</ref> One month later, Minho was chosen as a member of the group [[Shinee]], the five-member boy group debuted on May 25, 2008 on [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]' [[Inkigayo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=2008052520257|title = SM \ub300\ud615 \uc2e0\uc778 '\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8' 25\uc77c '\uc778\uae30\uac00\uc694' \ud1b5\ud574 \ub370\ubdd4|work=Digital News|date = August 20, 2008|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160711210954/http://hei.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=2008052520257|archivedate = 11 July 2016}}</ref> The group's first [[mini-album]], ''[[Replay (EP)|Replay]]'' was released on May 22 <ref name=\"shineetimes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2008/11/143_34146.html|title=SHINee Open to New Opportunities|publisher=Han, Sang-hee|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=November 25, 2008|date=November 10, 2008}}</ref> and debuted on the Korean music charts MIAK at #10<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090308020324/http://miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200805.htm|archivedate=March 8, 2009|url=http://miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200805.htm|title=May 2008 Album Sales|publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea|accessdate=March 8, 2009|language=ko}}</ref> and peaked at #8.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080718045228/http://miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200806.htm|archivedate=July 18, 2008|url=http://miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200806.htm|title=June 2008 Album Sales|publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea|accessdate=March 8, 2009|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 and 2010, Minho appeared in both the Korean and Japanese versions of [[Girls' Generation]]'s music video \"[[Gee (Girls' Generation song)|Gee]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gooddaysports.co.kr/news/?cset=star&bset=view&tot_code=47&code=3181|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506151052/http://www.gooddaysports.co.kr/news/?cset=star&bset=view&tot_code=47&code=3181|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 6, 2012|title=SHINee's Minho, Girls' Generation's \"Gee\"|work=Good Day Sports|accessdate=January 19, 2009|date=January 7, 2009|language=ko}}</ref> He was also featured in the music video of VNT's debut song ''Sound'' in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc2e0\uc778\uadf8\ub8f9 VNT \ubba4\ube44\uc5d0 \uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638 \uae5c\uc9dd \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ud654\uc81c|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0002056879|accessdate=May 19, 2013|newspaper=Naver|date=October 29, 2010|language=ko}}</ref> In 2009, Minho joined the popular show ''[[Let's Go! Dream Team Season 2|Let's Go! Dream Team]]'' as a regular member.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2009101515092390139|script-title=ko:\uc774\ucc3d\uba85 \"'\ucd9c\ubc1c\ub4dc\ub9bc\ud3002' \uc9c4\ud589, \ub354 \uc774\uc0c1\uc758 \uc18c\uc6d0\uc740 \uc5c6\ub2e4\"|work=Asiae News|date=October 15, 2009|author=Im, Hae Seon|accessdate=July 10, 2011|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\n===2010\u201315: Songwriting and acting debut===\nIn 2010, Minho made his acting debut in the [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS2]]'s drama special, entitled ''[[Pianist (Drama special)|Pianist]]'' with actress [[Han Ji-hye]].<ref name=\"Minho debut acting\">[http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2010110917090240721 SHINee Minho to make acting debut through KBS drama] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120925010226/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2010110917090240721 |date=September 25, 2012 }}. ''10Asia'' November 9, 2010. Retrieved November 13, 2010</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Minho was cast in SBS' sitcom, ''[[Salamander Guru and The Shadows]]''. He played the role of a genius hacker.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hwang|first=Gun Yong|script-title=ko:'\ub3c4\ub8e1\ub1fd\ub3c4\uc0ac' \ubbfc\ud638, \uccab \uc2dc\ud2b8\ucf64 \ub3c4\uc804 \ud569\uaca9\uc810..'\uc5f0\uae30\uae4c\uc9c0 \uc811\uc218'|url=http://www.segye.com/Articles/SPN/ENTERTAINMENTS/Article.asp?aid=20120128000025&subctg1=&subctg2=|accessdate=May 19, 2013|newspaper=SEGYE|date=January 28, 2012|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Minho was confirmed to be the lead role, alongside [[Sulli Choi|f(x)'s Sulli]] and [[Lee Hyun-woo (born 1993)|Lee Hyun-woo]], in ''[[To the Beautiful You]]'', Korean adaptation of \"[[Hana-Kimi|Hana Kimi]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=f(x)'s Sulli and SHINee's Minho Confirmed as Leads in \u2032Hana-Kimi\u2032 Remake|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/7575/fxs-sulli-and-shinees-minho-confirmed-as-leads-in-hana-kimi-remake|work=Mwave|accessdate=June 5, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20120426n09556?mid=e0101 |title=SM \uc81c\uc791 '\uc544\ub984\ub2e4\uc6b4 \uadf8\ub300\uc5d0\uac8c' SBS \ud3b8\uc131..\ubbfc\ud638-\uc124\ub9ac \uc8fc\uc5f0 : \ub124\uc774\ud2b8 \ub274\uc2a4|work=Nate News|date=April 26, 2012|accessdate=October 5, 2012|language=Korean}}</ref>\nThe drama started broadcasting on August 15, 2012 on [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SHINee's Minho Says He'll Overcome the Acting Controversies|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/12314/shinees-minho-says-hell-overcome-the-acting-controversies|archive-url=https://archive.today/20160629135636/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/12314/shinees-minho-says-hell-overcome-the-acting-controversies|url-status=dead|archive-date=June 29, 2016|accessdate=August 14, 2012|work=Mwave}}</ref> In preparation for his role as a high jump gold medalist, Minho received personal training from coach Kim Tae-young, former national high jump athlete and a member of the Korea Association of Athletics Federations, for a month and a half.<ref>{{in lang|ko}} [http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=109&aid=0002382768 '\uc544\uadf8\ub300' \ubbfc\ud638, \ub192\uc774\ub6f0\uae30 \uc120\uc218\ub85c \uc644\ubcbd '\ube59\uc758' :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \ub274\uc2a4]. Naver. (July 18, 2012). Retrieved on October 14, 2012.</ref> His personal record at the moment is 175&nbsp;cm.<ref>{{in lang|ko}} [http://star.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/OhmyStar/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0001759632 \uc544\ub984\ub2e4\uc6b4 \uadf8\ub300\uc5d0\uac8c> \ubbfc\ud638 \"\uc81c \ub192\uc774\ub6f0\uae30 \uae30\ub85d\uc740\uc694...\" \u2013 \uc624\ub9c8\uc774\uc2a4\ud0c0] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113154335/http://star.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/OhmyStar/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0001759632 |date=November 13, 2012 }}. ''Star News''. Retrieved on October 14, 2012.</ref>\n\nIn September 2012 JQ, who works under SM Entertainment to improve and direct the rapping abilities of their artists and used to be Shinee's rap instructor, praised Minho's writing ability and pointed out that he has many good ideas and \"a few genius moments here and there\". He was especially pleased with Minho's rap lyrics for Shinee's lead single \"[[Romeo (EP)|Juliette]]\" in 2009.<ref name=\"JQ\"/> Minho has been participating in the rap making of Shinee's songs since debut and has written and co-written several of the rap lyrics for Shinee's earlier songs like \"Love's Way\", \"[[Sanso Gateun Neo (Love Like Oxygen)|Love Like Oxygen]]\", \"Graze\", and \"Best Place\" in Shinee's debut album ''[[The Shinee World]]''. In addition to Shinee's second extended play ''[[Romeo (EP)|Romeo]]'' he assisted JQ with \"Talk to You\" and \"[[Romeo (EP)#Track list|Juliette]]\" in the rap making.<ref name=\"JQ\">{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20120923n07558|title=JQ \"\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638 \ub3c4\ub3c4\ud558\ub2e4\uace0? \uc228\uaca8\uc9c4 \uc2e4\uccb4\ub294..\"(\uc778\ud130\ubdf0)|trans-title=JQ, SM Entertainments rap instructor talks about Minho's personality + interview|work=Nate|publisher=Newsen|accessdate=July 18, 2017|date=September 23, 2012|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170718225433/http://news.nate.com/view/20120923n07558|archivedate=July 18, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2013, Minho returned to the small screen with [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s ''[[Medical Top Team]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jeon|first=Su Mi|title=SHINee\u2032s Minho Joins \u2032Medical Top Team\u2032 as Another Doctor|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/41957|work=MWave|accessdate=December 28, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029115419/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/41957|archive-date=October 29, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> The drama received low ratings and was criticized for trying to tell too many stories at once and losing the main focal point of the story<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kdramastars.com/articles/13048/20131213/medical-top-team-finale-failure-of-medical-drama.htm|title='Medical Top Team' Finale: Failure Of Medical Drama |work= |accessdate=July 19, 2017 |df=dmy|first=Angela|last=Son }}</ref> however Minho's acting performance received positive response and was praised for his growth as an actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2013110810592229701|script-title=ko:'\uba54\ub514\uceec \ud0d1\ud300' \ubbfc\ud638, \uac00\uc2b4 \uc6b8\ub9ac\ub294 \uc774\uc720\u2026\uc131\uc2e4\ud55c \uc5f0\uae30|trans-title='Medical top team' Minho, the reason for the chest ring ... Sincere acting|duplicate_work= |accessdate=July 19, 2017 |df=dmy|first=Young-joon|last=Jang|work=Asiae|language=ko }}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Minho was cast as the lead in [[OnStyle]]'s drama ''[[My First Time (TV series)|My First Time]]'' together with actress [[Park So-dam]], which was broadcast in September. It is the first drama premiered by OnStyle, with a total of eight episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=2015070353277 |title=OnStyle drama |work=Hankyung |accessdate=July 4, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706011533/http://www.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=2015070353277 |archivedate=July 6, 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201510051521050933161_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=SHINee's Minho talks about role, fellow cast members in new series 'My First Time'|date=October 5, 2015|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\n\n===2016\u2013present: Big screen debut, solo music and military enlistment===\n[[File:Choi Min-ho at Derailed press conference in November 2016 04.jpg|thumb|160px|right|Minho at the press conference for the movie ''[[Derailed (2016 film)|Derailed]]'' in November, 2016.]]\nIn early 2016, Minho extended his popularity as an actor. He was cast in several projects, including a historical Korean drama entitled ''[[Hwarang: The Poet Warrior Youth]]'', which was aired on December 19, 2016 on [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS2]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2016/12/19/67/0200000000AEN20161219005900315F.html|title=Idols explain their roles in drama 'Hwarang'|date=December 19, 2016|work=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref> His debut movie project titled ''[[Canola (film)|Canola]]'', alongside [[Youn Yuh-jung]] and [[Kim Go-eun]] and directed by Yoon Hong-seung (pseudonym Director Changwhich), was filmed in 2015 and was released on the big screen in May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3018767|title=SHINee singer Minho forays to the big screen|work=Korea Joongang Daily|accessdate=June 18, 2016|date=May 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160503000694|title=Long-lost granddaughter returns in 'Canola'|work=The Korea Herald|accessdate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/104637/bnt-photo-shinees-minho-talks-about-canola|title=SHINee\u2032s Minho Talks about \u2032Canola\u2032|work=Mwave|publisher=BNT News|accessdate=April 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160420145324/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/104637/bnt-photo-shinees-minho-talks-about-canola|archive-date=April 20, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The second one is a supporting role in a film entitled ''[[The Princess and the Matchmaker]]'', to be led by [[Lee Seung-gi]] and [[Shim Eun-kyung]]. The movie is the second installment in a planned trilogy by Jupiter Films after the 2013 box-office hit ''[[The Face Reader]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=SHIM Eun-kyoung and LEE Seung-gi' MARITAL HARMONY Began Shooting|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/news/news.jsp?mode=VIEW&seq=3583&blbdComCd=601006|website=Korean Film Council|accessdate=September 29, 2015|date=September 15, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ko:\uc2a4\ud3ec\uce20\uc870\uc120 :: \uc774\uc2b9\uae30-\uc2ec\uc740\uacbd, \uc601\ud654 '\uad81\ud569'\uc11c \ud638\ud761...\uc644\ubcbd '\ucf00\ubbf8' \uacfc\uc2dc\ud560\uae4c|trans-title=Lee Seung-gi, Shim Eun-kyung, film 'chemistry' perfect to show off|url = http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201507210100226600016114&servicedate=20150720|website =Sports Chosun|accessdate = November 4, 2015|author=Koo Jae-wan|language=ko}}</ref>\nChoi was then cast in the movie ''[[Derailed (2016 film)|Derailed]]'' alongside veteran actor [[Ma Dong-seok]], which is directed by Lee Seong-tae and premiered at [[2016 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web|script-title=ko:\ub9c8\ub3d9\uc11d\u00b7\ubbfc\ud638, \uc800\uc608\uc0b0\uc601\ud654 '\ub450 \ub0a8\uc790'\ub85c \ubb49\uce5c\ub2e4|trans-title=Min-ho and Dong-seok converge to low-budget film 'Two Men'|url = http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2016/01/13/2016011302174.html|author=Kim Kyoung Joo|website = Chosun|accessdate = January 13, 2016|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Cannes: South Korea's M-Line Presents K-Pop-Fueled 'No Way to Go' |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-south-koreas-m-line-892640 |work=The Hollywood Report |author=Lee Hyo-won |accessdate=August 23, 2016 |date=May 10, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823200113/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-south-koreas-m-line-892640 |archivedate=August 23, 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> The movie had its world premiere screening at the 21st [[Busan International Film Festival]] in October 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|title=BIFF \u2013 DERAILED (a.k.a. NO WAY TO GO) |url=http://www.biff.kr/eng/html/program/prog_view.asp?idx=23799&c_idx=288&sp_idx=423&QueryStep=2 |work=Busan International Film Festival |accessdate=September 30, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160930231302/http://www.biff.kr/eng/html/program/prog_view.asp?idx=23799&c_idx=288&sp_idx=423&QueryStep=2 |archivedate=September 30, 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Minho took part in the [[JTBC]] web drama entitled ''Somehow 18'' alongside [[Lee Yu-bi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20170531n11277?mid=n0107|title=\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, JTBC \uc6f9\ub4dc '\uc5b4\uca4c\ub2e4 18' \ub0a8\uc8fc\uc778\uacf5 \ud655\uc815 (\uacf5\uc2dd)|trans-title=SHINee's Minho Confirmed For Lead Role In Upcoming JTBC Rom-Com Drama |work=Nate News|accessdate=June 10, 2017|date=31 May 2017|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2017/08/398_235460.html|title=JTBC makes first web drama 'Somehow 18'|date=August 27, 2017|work=The Korea Times}}</ref> As a result of high online viewer ratings of more than 870,000 views, the web drama was announced to be broadcast on television through JTBC on 8 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=15057186961278404002|title='\uc54c\uc0ac\ub78c' '\ud799\ud55c\uc120\uc0dd' '\uc5b4\uca4c\ub2e418'\u2026JTBC \uc6f9\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8, \ucd94\uc11d TV\uc11c \ubcf8\ub2e4|trans-title='The Person You Could Know' 'Hip Hop Teacher' 'Somehow 18' JTBC Web dramas will be broadcast for Chuseok TV  |work=TV Daily|accessdate=September 19, 2017|date=September 18, 2017|author=Cho Hye-jin|language=ko}}</ref>\nAfter receiving positive response for his acting performance in ''Derailed'',<ref name=\"jinroh\"/> Minho was cast in science fiction action thriller ''[[Illang: The Wolf Brigade]]'', the Korean adaptation of the Japanese anime ''[[Jin-Roh: The Wolf Brigade]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Noh|first1=Jean|title='The Good, The Bad, The Weird' director Kim Jee-woon sets cast, shoot date for new sci-fi|url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/the-good-the-bad-the-weird-director-kim-jee-woon-sets-cast-shoot-date-for-new-sci-fi/5120039.article|website=Screen Dailyn|access-date=July 20, 2017|date=July 17, 2017}}</ref> The film released on July 25, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002800473&r|script-title=ko:'\uc778\ub791' \uac15\ub3d9\uc6d0\u2192\ucd5c\ubbfc\ud638, \uc2dc\uc120 \ub5c4 \uc218 \uc5c6\ub2e4 '\uc555\ub3c4\uc801 \ube44\uc8fc\uc5bc'  |trans-title= 'In-Rang' Kang Dong Won \u2192 Choi Min Ho, unable to keep eye on 'overwhelming visual'|work=Naver|accessdate=June 25, 2018|date=June 25, 2018|first=Jung-sun|last=Park|language=ko}}</ref><ref name=\"jinroh\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvreport.co.kr/?c=news&m=newsview&idx=997369|title='\uc778\ub791' \uac15\ub3d9\uc6d0x\ud55c\ud6a8\uc8fcx\uc815\uc6b0\uc131x\ubbfc\ud638\u2026\uafc8\uc758 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305 \ud655\uc815[\uacf5\uc2dd] |trans-title= Kang Dongwon x Han Hyo Ju x Jung Woo Sung x Min Ho ... Confirmed casting of dreams [Official]|work=TV Report|accessdate=July 18, 2017|date=July 18, 2017|first=Soo-jung|last=Kim|language=ko|quote= In addition, Choi Min-ho, who has set himself up as an actor through the impressive performance shown in 'Derailed', will portray 'Kim Chul-jin', a young talent specialist who always covers him right behind Lim Chung-kyung. Filming to begin in August 2017.}}</ref>\nIn September 2017, Choi received the Special Award at the [[:id:Indonesian Television Awards 2017|Indonesian Television Awards 2017]] due to his widespread popularity in the country as well as for his performances in various dramas. Minho was the first Korean artist to be presented an award at the show.<ref name=\"special award\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201709221350514929624_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=SHINee's Minho receives award at Indonesian Television Awards|date=September 22, 2017|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\nOn 15 November, Minho was included in [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'s list of ''\"Sexiest Men Alive\"''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/blake-shelton-unconventional-alternatives-to-2017-sexiest-man-alive|title=Blake Shelton May Be People's Sexiest Man Alive, But Here's Our List|work=Vogue|accessdate=November 17, 2017|date=November 15, 2017|author= Janelle Okwodu}}</ref>\nLater that year, Minho was cast in a four episode mini drama ''[[The Most Beautiful Goodbye]]'', which is a remake of the 1996 drama of the same name.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1OMD3QMAMS|script-title=ko:'\uc138\uc0c1\uc5d0\uc11c \uac00\uc7a5 \uc544\ub984\ub2e4\uc6b4 \uc774\ubcc4' \ucd5c\uc9c0\uc6b0-\ucd5c\ubbfc\ud638 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ud655\uc815 (\uacf5\uc2dd)|trans-title='The most beautiful farewell in the world' Choi Ji Woo - Choi Min Ho|work=SE Daily|accessdate=October 19, 2017|date=October 19, 2017|author=Jung Da-hoon|language=ko }}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Minho held his fan meeting tour, ''\"Best Choi's Minho\"'' covering four cities [[Seoul]] on February 16, [[Tokyo]] on February 23\u201324, [[Bangkok]] on March 2 and [[Taipei]] on March 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190109006900315?section=culture/entertainment#none|title=SHINee's Minho to go on a fan meeting tour of 4 nations|date=9 January 2019|work=[[Yonhap News Agency]]}}</ref> He concluded his tour with an additional fan meeting in [[Seoul]] on March 30.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3060156|title=SHINee\u2019s Minho to meet fans again|date=9 January 2019|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|author=Yoon So-yeon}}</ref> Minho released his debut solo single, \"I'm Home\", as part of [[SM Station]] on March 28.<ref name=\"Enlist\">{{cite web |url=https://entertain.v.daum.net/v/20190321103128046 |script-title=ko:\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, 4\uc6d415\uc77c \ud574\ubcd1\ub300 \uc785\ub300 \"\uc624\ub298(21\uc77c) \ud569\uaca9\"(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5) |trans-title=Shinee's Minho to Join the Marine Corps on April 15th |language=Korean |last=Kim |first=Yeeun |date=March 21, 2019 |website=[[Daum (web portal)|Daum]] |publisher= |access-date=March 21, 2019}}</ref> He joined the Marine Corps on April 15 for his [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military enlistment]].<ref name=\"Enlist\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0001099196 |script-title=ko:\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, \uc624\ub298(15\uc77c) \ud574\ubcd1\ub300 \uc785\ub300\u2026\ucd5c\uac15\ucc3d\ubbfc\u00b7\ud0dc\ubbfc\u00b7\uc218\ud638\u00b7\uaddc\ud604 \ubc30\uc6c5 [\uc885\ud569] |trans-title=Shinee's Minho Joins the Marine Corps Today, April 15th; Changmin, Taemin, Suho and Kyuhyun Send Him Off |language=Korean |last= |first= |date=April 15, 2019 |website=[[Naver]] |publisher= |access-date=April 15, 2019}}</ref> Minho's expected discharge date is November 14, 2020.\n\n==Personal life==\n{{quotebox|width=25em|align=right|\"I wanted to become a professional football player like my dad, [...] But when I was a fifth grader, he told me he would kick me out of the house if I pursue that dream. That was the first time he disapproved of something I did so I decided to give up the dream.\"|source=\u2013Minho about his dreams and the relationship with his father.<ref name=\"koreadaily\"/>}}\nMinho graduated from [[Konkuk University]]'s affiliated high school on February 10, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\ubbfc\ud638 \ub450 \uc190 \ubaa8\uc544 \ubd80\ub974\ub294 \uc560\uad6d\uac00 |url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=4008351&ctg=|accessdate=June 21, 2016|work=Ilgan Sports|date=February 10, 2010|language=ko}}</ref>  After taking the college admissions test the previous year, he was admitted in 2010 to Konkuk's part-time admittance for the arts and culture film major and graduated in 2015.<ref>{{in lang|ko}}[http://www.todaykorea.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=96514 \uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, \uac74\uad6d\ub300 \uc815\uc2dc \ud569\uaca9 ] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20120917112255/http://www.todaykorea.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=96514 |date=September 17, 2012 }} ''Today Korea''. Retrieved December 15, 2010.</ref> His father, [[Choi Yun-kyum]], is a well-known South Korean soccer coach. Minho inherited his father's ability and showed his skills in shows like [[KBS2]]'s ''Our Town's Physical Variety'' and won high praise from [[Lee Young-pyo]], a retired member of the national team. Minho also led his team to victory at the Idol Futsal World Cup Competition.<ref>{{cite web|title=What if idols were soccer players?|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140616001202_2|accessdate=June 21, 2016|work= Kpop Herald|date=May 14, 2014}}</ref> Originally Minho wanted to become a professional football player like his father but he disapproved of his decision stating: \"Frankly, I didn't want him to follow my path, [...] Back when I was playing, it was difficult to make it in that world, very abusive back in those days. I would stay home for a couple of hours and then be off to training camp. It pained me to see my son asking me to stay over for the night.\". His father also added that from the football manager's point of view, he didn't think his son had it in him to make it in that field stating Minho is a strong-willed person, but has a small frame.<ref name=\"koreadaily\">{{cite web|title=In football and K-pop, like father, like son|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3026749|accessdate=November 29, 2016|work= Korea Joongang Daily|date=November 29, 2016|last=Park|first=Lin}}</ref>\n\n==Ambassador roles==\nIn 2011, he was named an Honorary Ambassador for Youth 2011.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, '\uccad\uc18c\ub144 \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \uc704\ucd09' |url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/news/view.html?gid=G1105230159|accessdate=June 21, 2016|work= Osen|date=May 25, 2011|language=ko}}</ref> Three years later in 2014, Minho and [[Im Yoona|Yoona]] were appointed as [[UNICEF]] Unihero Campaign Ambassadors \"Giving Hope to the Children\".<ref>{{cite web|title=SHINee, Girls' Generation stars promote UNICEF |url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2014/12/113_169938.html|accessdate=June 21, 2016|work=The Korea Times|date=December 15, 2012}}</ref> In the same year, Minho was listed among the Top Korean Stars, receiving 300 million won as his annual advertising rate.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u4e2d\ub300\ub959 \ub4a4\ud754\ub4e0 \uae40\uc218\ud604\u00b7\uc774\ubbfc\ud638, CF 10\uc5b5 '\ud6cc\uca4d'|url=http://www.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=2014103131241|accessdate=June 21, 2016|work= Hankyung|date=November 11, 2014|language=ko}}</ref> In 2016, Minho was part of [[UNICEF]]'s ''#IMAGINE'' campaign, which was first introduced in November 2014 to commemorate the 25th anniversary of the United Nation's [[Convention on the Rights of the Child]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Nguyen|last=Minh|title=Korean Pop Stars Join UNICEF's #IMAGINE Project|work=NBC News|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/korean-pop-stars-join-unicef-s-imagine-project-n601066|date=June 29, 2016|accessdate=July 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, Choi together with the [[First Lady of the United States]] [[Melania Trump]] attended the \"Girls Play 2\" campaign at the US embassy in Korea, an event organised to promote [[2018 Winter Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Eun-byel|last=Im|title=Melania Trump meets Minho of Shinee|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|url=http://nwww.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20171107000880|accessdate=November 8, 2017|date=November 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Annie|last=Martin|title=Melania Trump meets Shinee singer Minho in South Korea|work=[[United Press International|UPI]]|url=https://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2017/11/07/Melania-Trump-meets-Shinee-singer-Minho-in-South-Korea/4591510075739/|accessdate=November 8, 2017|date=November 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2012 || ''[[I Am (2012 film)|I Am]]'' || rowspan=\"2\"| Himself || Biographical film of [[SM Town]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Documentary Shows Top K-Pop Singers Behind the Scenes |url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2012/05/02/2012050200829.html |accessdate=May 4, 2012 |newspaper=The Chosun Ilbo |date=May 2, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2015 || ''SMTOWN The Stage'' || Documentary of [[SM Town]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/film-tv/article/1882530/film-review-smtown-stage-k-pop-love-exo-girls-generation-super |title=Film review: SMTown: The Stage |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |date=November 24, 2015 |first=Edmund |last=Lee |accessdate=April 8, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2016 ||''[[Canola (film)|Canola]]'' || Han-i  ||\n|-\n|[[Derailed (2016 film)|''Derailed'']]|| Jin-il ||\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018 ||''[[The Princess and the Matchmaker]]'' || Seo Ga-yoon ||\n|-\n| ''[[Illang: The Wolf Brigade]]'' || Kim Cheol-jin  ||\n|-\n| rowspan=1|2019||''[[The Battle of Jangsari]]'' || Choi Seung-pil ||<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/megan-fox-to-appear-in-korean-war-movie-jangsa-ri-1202937869/|title=Megan Fox to Appear in Korean War Movie \u2018Jangsa-ri\u2019|quote=Alongside Fox, veteran Korean actor Kim Myung-min (\u201cV.I.P.\u201d) and rapper-turned-actor Choi Min-ho (\u201cIllang: The Wolf Brigade\u201d) of K-pop boyband Shinee will also appear in the movie.|last=Kil|first=Sonia|date=2018-09-12|work=Variety|access-date=September 24, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[My Precious You]]'' || Himself || rowspan=2| [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS2]] || Special appearance\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Pianist (TV special)|Pianist]]'' || Oh Je-ro || Drama special\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2012 || ''[[Salamander Guru and The Shadows]]'' || Choi Min-hyuk ||  rowspan=2| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] || Sitcom\n|-\n|''[[To The Beautiful You]]'' || Kang Tae-joon ||\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Medical Top Team]]'' || Kim Seong-woo || [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[My First Time (TV series)|My First Time]]'' || Yoon Tae-oh || [[OnStyle]] ||\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Drinking Solo]]'' || Himself || [[TVN (South Korea)|tvN]] || Cameo<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201609201528585100359_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=SHINee's Minho bu