014 }}</ref>\n|-\n|  rowspan=\"1\"|[[MBC Entertainment Awards]] || rowspan=\"1\"| Popularity Award (Music Talk Show) || rowspan= \"1\" | ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' || rowspan=\"1\" {{won}} || <ref>{{cite news | language=ko | url=http://joynews.inews24.com/php/news_view.php?g_menu=700100&g_serial=873498 |work=Joy News | title=[MBC \uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c1]\uc720\uc7ac\uc11d \ub300\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1\u2026'\uc9c4\uc9dc\uc0ac\ub098\uc774' 9\uad00\uc655(\uc885\ud569)| date=December 12, 2014|accessdate=August 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | language=ko | url=http://news.joins.com/article/19326372 | work=JoongAng Ilbo | title='\uc74c\uc911' \uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638 \uc778\uae30\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1 \"\uadf8\ub140\uc11d \ud615\uc5d0\uac8c\ub3c4 \uace0\ub9d9\ub2e4\"[MBC\uc5f0\uc608\ub300\uc0c12015] | date=December 29, 2015 | accessdate=August 27, 2016 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827084926/http://news.joins.com/article/19326372 | archivedate=August 27, 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2017 || Indonesian Television Awards || Special Award || {{NA}} || {{won}} ||<ref name=\"special award\">{{cite news | url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110736471 |work=JoongAng Ilbo| script-title=ko:\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638, \uc778\ub3c4\ub124\uc2dc\uc548 \uc2dc\uc0c1\uc2dd\uc11c \uc218\uc0c1..\"\u97d3\uac00\uc218 \uc911 \uc720\uc77c\"|trans-title=SHINee's Minho Receives Special Award At Indonesian Television Awards 2017|author=Lee So-dam|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170921165527/http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110736471|archivedate=September 21, 2017| date=September 21, 2017 | language=ko }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[54th Grand Bell Awards]]|| Best New Actor|| ''[[Derailed (2016 film)|Derailed]]'' || {{nom}} ||<ref>{{cite news | url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000597219&spi_ref=m_entertain_twitter |work=Naver| script-title=ko:\uc81c54\ud68c \ub300\uc885\uc0c1\uc601\ud654\uc81c \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc791 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026'\ub354 \ud0b9'\ubd80\ud130 '\ud0dd\uc2dc\uc6b4\uc804\uc0ac'\uae4c\uc9c0 |trans-title=Nominees for the 54th Grand Bell Awards revealed | date=September 29, 2017|author= Jo Youkyung | language=ko }}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|3rd [[Asia Artist Awards]]\n|Asia Brilliant Award\n|{{NA}}\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/11/28/bts-win-the-daesang-at-asia-artist-awards-2018-and-are-among-artists-of-the-year-8187121/|title=BTS win the Daesang at Asia Artist Awards 2018 \u2013 and are among Artists Of The Year|date=November 28, 2018|website=Metro}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Shinee discography]]\n*[[List of awards and nominations received by Shinee]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://shinee.smtown.com Shinee Official website]\n\n{{Shinee}}\n{{SM Entertainment}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Choi, Min-ho}}\n[[Category:Shinee members]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male rappers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television presenters]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean male actors]]\n[[Category:Konkuk University alumni]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Incheon]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "136.228.172.200", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Choi_Min-ho"}
{"title_page": "Our Lady of Assumption Church, Pragasapuram", "text_new": "<br />{{Infobox church\n| name                   = Our Lady of Assumption Church, Pragasapuram\n| fullname               = \n| image                  = Rc Church Pragasapuram.jpg\n| imagesize              =\n\n| caption                = Our Lady of Assumption Church \n| latd                   = \n| latm                   = \n| lats                   = \n| latNS                  = \n| longd                  = \n| longm                  = \n| longs                  = \n| longEW                 = \n| coordinates            = {{coord|8.560715|77.971978|display=inline,title}}\n| location               = [[Pragasapuram]]\n| country                = [[India]]\n| denomination           = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| previous denomination  =\n| churchmanship          = \n| membership             = \n| attendance             = \n| website                = \n| former name            = \n| bull date              = \n| founded date           = 15th August 1880\n| founder                = \n| dedication             = \n| dedicated date         = \n| consecrated date       = 21st November 1967\n| cult                   = \n| relics                 = \n| events                 = Holy Mass, Eucharist\n| past bishop            = \n| people                 = \n| status                 = [[Parish Church]]\n| functional status      = Active\n| heritage designation   = Parish \n| designated date        = 1909\n| architect              = \n| architectural type     =\n| style                  = \n| groundbreaking         = \n| completed date         = \n| construction cost      =\n| closed date            = \n| demolished date        = \n| capacity               = \n| length                 = \n| width                  = \n| width nave             = \n| height                 = \n| diameter               = \n| other dimensions       = \n| floor count            = \n| floor area             = \n| spire quantity         = \n| spire height           = \n| materials              = \n| parish                 = \n| deanery                = \n| archdeaconry           = \n| archdiocese            = \n| diocese                = \n| province               = \n| presbytery             = \n| synod                  = \n| circuit                = \n| district               = Tuticorin\n| division               = Sathankulam\n| subdivision            = Pragasapuram\n| archbishop             = \n| bishop                 = [[Most.Rev.Dr.A.Stephen]]\n| dean                   = \n| subdean                = \n| provost                = \n| provost-rector         = \n| viceprovost            = \n| canon                  = \n| canonpastor            = \n| precentor              = \n| archdeacon             = \n| prebendary             = \n| rector                 = \n| vicar                  = \n| curate                 = \n| priestincharge         = Fr.Antony Irudhaya Thomas\n| asstpriest             = \n| minister               = \n| assistant              = \n| honpriest              = \n| deacon                 = \n| deaconness             = \n| seniorpastor           = \n| pastor                 = \n| abbot                  = \n| chaplain               = \n| reader                 = \n| organistdom            = \n| director               = \n| organist               = \n| organscholar           = \n| chapterclerk           = \n| laychapter             = \n| warden                 = \n| flowerguild            = \n| musicgroup             = \n| parishadmin            = \n| serversguild           = \n| logo                   = \n| logosize               = \n}}\n\n'''Our Lady of Assumption Church'''  is a Roman Catholic church.It is the [[Parish]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tuticorin]]. And it has 7 Sub-Parishes.\n\n= History =\nHistory states that in 1979 there were 14 Catholic families in [[Pragasapuram]]. Initially Pragasapuram was the Sub-Parish of the Sathankulam Parish. In 15-08-1880, Our Lady of Assumption Chapel was opened by Fr.Denish Kushan. The first Car Procession of Our Lady of Assumption was held on 15-08-1895. At that time there was 3 Chapparam. Devotees carry it on their shoulders. In 1907, [[Arthur Margoschis]] (Father of Nazareth) presented the Holy Cross of Jesus Christ that he kept in his Prayer hall,\u00a0 to the Our Lady of Assumption Church, Pragasapuram. \n\nIn 1909, Pragasapuram became an independent Parish. Sub-Parishes separated from the [[Sathankulam]] and [[Punnaikayal]] Parishes were merged with the Pragasapuram Parish. The foundation stone for New Church was laid in 1913 by Fr.T.Michael. After the completion of the New Church foundation work, the Church building work was stopped. Thus the Holy Mass was conducted in the Old Our Lady of Assumption Chapel. Many years later the New Church was built and the New Church was opened by Bishop.Rev.Fr.Thomas on 21-11-1967.As the days went by, In 1975 during Fr.Cruz Mariyan period, Chapparam was replaced by Chariot. In the feasts that followed, the devotees\u00a0 celebrated the Annual Feast of Our Lady of Assumption by pulling the St.Mary's Chariot.\n\nSt. Mary's Kebi was built on 11-08-1980 at the site of the Old Our Lady of Assumption Chapel to commemorate the Century year (1880- 1980) of Our Lady of Assumption Chapel. The new Church altar was refurbished and the floors replaced with marbles when Fr.Jackson was a Parish Priest. In the 25th year of the construction of the St.Mary's Century Kebi, it was restored and renovated by Fr.A.S.Raja on 14-08-2007\n\n= Sub Parishes =\n\n1. Our Lady of Good Health Church, Madhavanam\n\n2. St.Joseph's Church, Kandhasamypuram\n\n3. Sacred Heart of Jesus Church, Pillayanmanai\n\n4. Our Lady of Lourdes Church, Udayarkulam\n\n5. Our Lady of Lourdes Church, Thoppur\n\n6. St. Antony's Church, Themankulam\n\n7. St. Antony's Church, Kurippankulam\n\n= Festivals =\n\n== St.Mary's Annual Feast ==\n\n[[File:Flag pole of olap.jpeg|thumb|right|Flagpole of Church]]\nThe Church Parish is celebrating the Our Lady of Assumption Annual Feast in a grand manner. St.Mary's Flag hoisting was held on 6th August every year. Followed by that they celebrating the festival for 10 days. 9th and 10th day of the Feast is an Important day of Our Lady of Assumption.\n[[File:Olap chariot.jpeg|thumb|right|St.Mary's Chariot]]\nCar procession was held on 14th and 15th of August every year. On 9th day(August 14) of Feast, Eucharistic Adoration service was held at the Church premises.On 10th day(August 15) of Feast, the Grand Holy Mass was held at the Church. Flag Lowering was held on end of the Feast(15th August-Night).\n\n== Samabanthi ==\nChurch provides free Food(Commonly known as Asanam or Samabanthi) for all people thrice a year in following dates.\n\n1. First Saturday of May month\n\n2. 16th August\n\n3. 29th September\n\n== Christmas ==\nThey celebrate Christmas by conducting Carols and Holy Mass. They built a Christmas Crib inside the church that reminds the Birth of Jesus.\n\n== Easter == \nThey celebrate Easter by conducting a Holy Mass on 12:00 am.They placed a Resurrection of Jesus statue to reminds the Resurrection of Jesus.\n\n= Chapels = \n1. St. Mary's Chapel\n[[File:Arputha kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|St.Mary's Chapel]]\n2. St. Antony's Chapel\n[[File:Antony kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|St. Antony's Chapel]]\n3. St. Michael's Chapel\n[[File:Michael kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|St. Michael's Chapel]]\n4. Our Lady of Good Health Chapel \n[[File:Velankanni kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|Our Lady of Good Health Chapel]]\n\n= Schools =\nTotally 4 schools were managed by our Parish.\n\n1. St.Mary's Middle School, Pragasapuram \n\n2. St. Joseph Primary School, Kandasamipuram\n\n3. R.C. Primary School, Thoppur\n\n4. R.C. Primary School, Udayarkulam \n\n= Wedding Hall =\n\n[[File:Marys mahal.jpeg|thumb|right|St.Mary's Mahal]]\nIt was a long-standing desire of the Pragasapuram Parish peoples to have a Wedding Hall of our own. As a result, in 2003 the foundation work was started by Fr. Arul Jackson. Most.Rev.Bishop.Yuvon Ambrose laid the foundation stone for St. Mary's Mahal. The pillars were erected and the concrete work was completed in Fr.Arul Jackson period. During the period of Fr.A.S.Raja, the First Floor was completed. Fr. Antony Duglas completed the St. Mary's  Mahal project with his efforts. Afterwards, during St.Mary's Annual Feast on 15-08-2013 Most.Rev.Bishop.Yuvon Ambrose blessed the Mahal and Aachi Masala Founder Mr.A.D. Padmasingh Isac opened the St. Mary's Mahal.\n\n= Convent =\nServite Convent, Pragasapuram\n[[Category:Catholic Church]]\n\n= Reference =\n<ref>http://catholicchurches.in/directory/tuticorin-churches/our-lady-of-assumption-church-pragasapuram.htm  </ref>\n", "text_old": "<br />{{Infobox church\n| name                   = Our Lady of Assumption Church, Pragasapuram\n| fullname               = \n| image                  = Rc Church Pragasapuram.jpg\n| imagesize              =\n\n| caption                = Our Lady of Assumption Church \n| latd                   = \n| latm                   = \n| lats                   = \n| latNS                  = \n| longd                  = \n| longm                  = \n| longs                  = \n| longEW                 = \n| coordinates            = {{coord|8.560715|77.971978|display=inline,title}}\n| location               = [[Pragasapuram]]\n| country                = [[India]]\n| denomination           = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| previous denomination  =\n| churchmanship          = \n| membership             = \n| attendance             = \n| website                = \n| former name            = \n| bull date              = \n| founded date           = 15th August 1880\n| founder                = \n| dedication             = \n| dedicated date         = \n| consecrated date       = 21st November 1967\n| cult                   = \n| relics                 = \n| events                 = Holy Mass, Eucharist\n| past bishop            = \n| people                 = \n| status                 = [[Parish Church]]\n| functional status      = Active\n| heritage designation   = Parish \n| designated date        = 1909\n| architect              = \n| architectural type     =\n| style                  = \n| groundbreaking         = \n| completed date         = \n| construction cost      =\n| closed date            = \n| demolished date        = \n| capacity               = \n| length                 = \n| width                  = \n| width nave             = \n| height                 = \n| diameter               = \n| other dimensions       = \n| floor count            = \n| floor area             = \n| spire quantity         = \n| spire height           = \n| materials              = \n| parish                 = \n| deanery                = \n| archdeaconry           = \n| archdiocese            = \n| diocese                = \n| province               = \n| presbytery             = \n| synod                  = \n| circuit                = \n| district               = Tuticorin\n| division               = Sathankulam\n| subdivision            = Pragasapuram\n| archbishop             = \n| bishop                 = [[Most.Rev.Dr.A.Stephen]]\n| dean                   = \n| subdean                = \n| provost                = \n| provost-rector         = \n| viceprovost            = \n| canon                  = \n| canonpastor            = \n| precentor              = \n| archdeacon             = \n| prebendary             = \n| rector                 = \n| vicar                  = \n| curate                 = \n| priestincharge         = Fr.Antony Irudhaya Thomas\n| asstpriest             = \n| minister               = \n| assistant              = \n| honpriest              = \n| deacon                 = \n| deaconness             = \n| seniorpastor           = \n| pastor                 = \n| abbot                  = \n| chaplain               = \n| reader                 = \n| organistdom            = \n| director               = \n| organist               = \n| organscholar           = \n| chapterclerk           = \n| laychapter             = \n| warden                 = \n| flowerguild            = \n| musicgroup             = \n| parishadmin            = \n| serversguild           = \n| logo                   = \n| logosize               = \n}}\n\n'''Our Lady of Assumption Church'''  is a Roman Catholic church.It is the [[Parish]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tuticorin]]. And it has 7 Sub-Parishes.\n\n= History =\nHistory states that in 1979 there were 14 Catholic families in [[Pragasapuram]]. Initially Pragasapuram was the Sub-Parish of the Sathankulam Parish. In 15-08-1880, Our Lady of Assumption Chapel was opened by Fr.Denish Kushan. The first Car Procession of Our Lady of Assumption was held on 15-08-1895. At that time there was 3 Chapparam. Devotees carry it on their shoulders. In 1907, [[Arthur Margoschis]] (Father of Nazareth) presented the Holy Cross of Jesus Christ that he kept in his Prayer hall,\u00a0 to the Our Lady of Assumption Church, Pragasapuram. \n\nIn 1909, Pragasapuram became an independent Parish. Sub-Parishes separated from the [[Sathankulam]] and [[Punnaikayal]] Parishes were merged with the Pragasapuram Parish. The foundation stone for New Church was laid in 1913 by Fr.T.Michael. After the completion of the New Church foundation work, the Church building work was stopped. Thus the Holy Mass was conducted in the Old Our Lady of Assumption Chapel. Many years later the New Church was built and the New Church was opened by Bishop.Rev.Fr.Thomas on 21-11-1967.As the days went by, In 1975 during Fr.Cruz Mariyan period, Chapparam was replaced by Chariot. In the feasts that followed, the devotees\u00a0 celebrated the Annual Feast of Our Lady of Assumption by pulling the St.Mary's Chariot.\n\nSt. Mary's Kebi was built on 11-08-1980 at the site of the Old Our Lady of Assumption Chapel to commemorate the Century year (1880- 1980) of Our Lady of Assumption Chapel. The new Church altar was refurbished and the floors replaced with marbles when Fr.Jackson was a Parish Priest. In the 25th year of the construction of the St.Mary's Century Kebi, it was restored and renovated by Fr.A.S.Raja on 14-08-2007\n\n= Sub Parishes =\n\n1. Our Lady of Good Health Church, Madhavanam\n\n2. St.Joseph's Church, Kandhasamypuram\n\n3. Sacred Heart of Jesus Church, Pillayanmanai\n\n4. Our Lady of Lourdes Church, Udayarkulam\n\n5. Our Lady of Lourdes Church, Thoppur\n\n6. St. Antony's Church, Themankulam\n\n7. St. Antony's Church, Kurippankulam\n\n= Festivals =\n\n== St.Mary's Annual Feast ==\n\n[[File:Flag pole of olap.jpeg|thumb|right|Flagpole of Church]]\nThe Church Parish is celebrating the Our Lady of Assumption Annual Feast in a grand manner. St.Mary's Flag hoisting was held on 6th August every year. Followed by that they celebrating the festival for 10 days. 9th and 10th day of the Feast is an Important day of Our Lady of Assumption.\n[[File:Olap chariot.jpeg|thumb|right|St.Mary's Chariot]]\nCar procession was held on 14th and 15th of August every year. On 9th day(August 14) of Feast, Eucharistic Adoration service was held at the Church premises.On 10th day(August 15) of Feast, the Grand Holy Mass was held at the Church. Flag Lowering was held on end of the Feast(15th August-Night).\n\n== Samabanthi ==\nChurch provides free Food(Commonly known as Asanam or Samabanthi) for all people thrice a year in following dates.\n\n1. First Saturday of May month\n\n2. 16 August\n\n3. 29 September\n\n== Christmas ==\nThey celebrate Christmas by conducting Carols and Holy Mass. They built a Christmas Crib inside the church that reminds the Birth of Jesus.\n\n== Easter == \nThey celebrate Easter by conducting a Holy Mass on 12:00 am.They placed a Resurrection of Jesus statue to reminds the Resurrection of Jesus.\n\n= Chapels = \n1. St. Mary's Chapel\n[[File:Arputha kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|St.Mary's Chapel]]\n2. St. Antony's Chapel\n[[File:Antony kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|St. Antony's Chapel]]\n3. St. Michael's Chapel\n[[File:Michael kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|St. Michael's Chapel]]\n4. Our Lady of Good Health Chapel \n[[File:Velankanni kebi.jpeg|thumb|right|Our Lady of Good Health Chapel]]\n\n= Schools =\nTotally 4 schools were managed by our Parish.\n\n1. St.Mary's Middle School, Pragasapuram \n\n2. St. Joseph Primary School, Kandasamipuram\n\n3. R.C. Primary School, Thoppur\n\n4. R.C. Primary School, Udayarkulam \n\n= Wedding Hall =\n\n[[File:Marys mahal.jpeg|thumb|right|St.Mary's Mahal]]\nIt was a long-standing desire of the Pragasapuram Parish peoples to have a Wedding Hall of our own. As a result, in 2003 the foundation work was started by Fr. Arul Jackson. Most.Rev.Bishop.Yuvon Ambrose laid the foundation stone for St. Mary's Mahal. The pillars were erected and the concrete work was completed in Fr.Arul Jackson period. During the period of Fr.A.S.Raja, the First Floor was completed. Fr. Antony Duglas completed the St. Mary's  Mahal project with his efforts. Afterwards, during St.Mary's Annual Feast on 15-08-2013 Most.Rev.Bishop.Yuvon Ambrose blessed the Mahal and Aachi Masala Founder Mr.A.D. Padmasingh Isac opened the St. Mary's Mahal.\n\n= Convent =\nServite Convent, Pragasapuram\n[[Category:Catholic Church]]\n\n= Reference =\n<ref>http://catholicchurches.in/directory/tuticorin-churches/our-lady-of-assumption-church-pragasapuram.htm  </ref>\n", "name_user": "Snowgift111", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSamabanthi", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Our_Lady_of_Assumption_Church,_Pragasapuram"}
{"title_page": "Seventeen (South Korean band)", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean boy group}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Seventeen\n| background      = group_or_band\n| image           = 180716 Seveteen performing \"Oh My!\" at You Make My Day Showcase.png\n| image_size      =\n| landscape       = yes\n| alt             = \n| caption         = Seventeen performing \"Oh My!\" in July 2018<br />Top row: Woozi, Wonwoo, Vernon, Mingyu, [[Wen Junhui|Jun]], Hoshi, [[The8]], and DK<br />Bottom row: Joshua, Jeonghan, Dino, S.Coups, and [[Seungkwan]] \n| alias           = \n| origin          = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[K-pop]]\n* [[synthpop]]\n* [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| years_active    = {{start date|2015}}\u2013present\n| label           = Pledis Entertainment\n| associated_acts = [[Bumzu]], BooSeokSoon\n| website         = {{url|http://www.pledis.co.kr/html/artist/seventeen|Korean Website}}<br />{{url|https://seventeen-17.jp/|Japanese Website}}\n| current_members = \n*S.Coups\n*Jeonghan\n*Joshua\n*[[Wen Junhui|Jun]]\n*Hoshi\n*Wonwoo\n*Woozi\n*DK\n*Mingyu\n*[[The8]]\n*[[Seungkwan]]\n*Vernon\n*Dino\n}}\n'''Seventeen''' ({{Korean|hangul=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4}}), also stylized as '''SEVENTEEN''' or '''SVT''', is a South Korean boy band formed by [[Pledis Entertainment]] in 2015. The group consists of 13 members divided into three sub-units, each with a different area of specialization: 'Hip-Hop Unit', 'Vocal Unit', and 'Performance Unit'. Seventeen has released three studio albums and six extended plays.\n\nSeventeen is considered a \"self-producing\" [[Korean pop idol|idol group]], with the members being actively involved in the songwriting, choreographing, and other aspects of the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20150526000750|title=Seventeen hopes to shine like diamonds with '17 Carat'|date=2015-05-26|website=The Korea Herald|accessdate=2016-05-09}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7356946/seventeen-first-loveletter-album-world-heatseekers-charts|title=Seventeen Send Their 'First Love&Letter' to Top 5 of World & Heatseekers Album Charts|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2016-05-04|website=Billboard|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2013\u20132015: Formation and early years===\n\n====''Seventeen TV''====\n{{Main|Seventeen TV}}\nStarting in 2013, Seventeen appeared in regular live broadcasts of a show called ''Seventeen TV'' on the online streaming platform [[UStream]]. The show had multiple seasons in which the trainees were introduced and shown practicing performances, with some seasons ending in ''Like Seventeen'' concerts.<ref>{{cite news|work=HEI|language=korean|url=http://hei.hankyung.com/hub02/201311263531q|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uc138 \ubc88\uc9f8 \ucf58\uc2a4\ud2b8, \ub2e4\uc591\ud55c \ubb34\ub300\ub85c \ud32c\ub4e4 \ub9e4\ub8cc|trans-title= Seventeen's third concert, captivated fans with various stages|date=November 23, 2013|accessdate=March 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|work=OSEN|language=korean|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109927555|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub370\ubdd4\uc804 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uc5f0\ub2e4..'\ucd5c\uc885 \uc810\uac80' |trans-title=Seventeen, last concert before debut revealed...'the final check'|date=August 12, 2014|accessdate=March 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====''Big Debut Plan''====\nPrior to debut, Seventeen also appeared in the reality TV show ''Seventeen Project: Big Debut Plan'', broadcast on [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] between May 2\u201326, 2015. The show concluded with the group's debut showcase.<ref name=\"naver1\">{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000466732|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8' \uccab \ubc29\uc1a1\u202613\u8272 \ub9e4\ub825 \ub2f4\uc558\ub2e4 '\ub9ac\uc5bc+\uc5f4\uc815'|last=|first=|date=2015-05-02|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-31}}</ref>\n\n====''Debut''====\n[[File:Seventeen (\uc138\ube10\ud2f4) at 2015 Summer K-POP Festival.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Seventeen performing at the 2015 Summer K-POP Festival at the [[Seoul Plaza]].]]\nSeventeen debuted on May 26 with a live showcase televised by MBC. They were the first male K-pop group to debut with a one-hour live showcase on a major broadcasting channel, with label-mates [[Lizzy (singer)|Lizzy]] and [[Raina (singer)|Raina]] serving as [[Master of ceremonies|MC]]<nowiki/>s.<ref name=\"The Korea Herald\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20150526000750|title=Seventeen hopes to shine like diamonds with '17 Carat'|last=Won|first=Ho-jung|date=2015-05-26|website=The Korea Herald|publisher=|accessdate=June 21, 2015}}</ref> Three days later, their first EP ''[[17 Carat]]'' was digitally released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6582987/seventeen-adore-u-13-member-boy-band|title=Here's What a 13-Member K-Pop Boy Band Looks Like: Watch 'Adore U' by Seventeen|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2015-05-30|website=Billboard|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-15}}</ref> ''17 Carat'' became the longest-charting K-pop album of the year in the US<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2015/12/kpop-debuts-rookies-best#1|title=K-Pop's 2015 Rookies: Who's Working It, & Who Needs Work|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2015-12-22|website=Fuse|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-15}}</ref> and was the only rookie album to appear on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s \"10 Best K-Pop Albums of 2015\" chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6828137/best-k-pop-albums-2015|title=The 10 Best K-Pop Albums of 2015|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|last2=Oak|first2=Jessica|date=2015-12-30|website=Billboard|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/101572/seventeen-is-only-rookie-group-to-make-billboards-best-k-pop-albums-list|title=KPOP NEWS \u2013 Seventeen is Only Rookie Group to Make Billboard\u2032s Best K-Pop Albums List {{!}} Mwave|last=Kim|first=JiYeon|date=2016-01-16|website=Mwave|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-09}}</ref>\n\nOn September 10 their second EP ''[[Boys Be (EP)|Boys Be]]'' was released, which would later become the highest selling rookie album of 2015.<ref name=\"2015\ub144 38\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart\">{{cite web | title = 2015\ub144 38\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart | author =  | publisher = [[Gaon Chart]] | date =  | accessdate = September 22, 2015 | url = http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=38&hitYear=2015&termGbn=week | language = ko }}</ref> The album's success earned the group awards at the [[Golden Disk Awards]], [[Seoul Music Awards]], and [[Gaon Chart K-Pop Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.sg/seventeen-return-brand-new-album-1918|title=Seventeen to return with a brand new album|last=Kaur|first=Gunjeet|date=2016-06-15|website=International Business Times|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003240481|title=\uc544\uc774\ucf58\u00b7\uc138\ube10\ud2f4\u00b7\uc5ec\uc790\uce5c\uad6c, \uc2e0\uc778\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1 [25th \uc11c\uc6b8\uac00\uc694\ub300\uc0c1]|last=|first=|date=2016-01-14|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Seventeen was also the only K-pop group on [[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'s \"21 Under 21 2015: Music's Hottest Young Stars\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=404&aid=0000118634|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, '\ube4c\ubcf4\ub4dc 21 Under 21' \uc544\uc2dc\uc544 \uac00\uc218 \uc720\uc77c \uc120\uc815|last=|first=|date=2015-11-01|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/6745079/billboard-21-under-21-2015-hottest-young-stars/6|title=Billboard's 21 Under 21 2015: Music's Hottest Young Stars|last=Partridge|first=Kenneth|date=2015-10-30|website=Billboard|publisher=|accessdate=October 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen held a four-date concert series titled ''2015 Like Seventeen \u2013 Boys Wish'' from the 24th to the 26th of December as an end-of-year celebration in Seoul.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003208833|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uccab \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8, \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508 1\ubd84 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub9e4\uc9c4..'\uae30\uc5fc'|last=|first=|date=2015-11-24|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> After the concerts' success, Seventeen held two related concerts the following February in 2016, entitled ''Like Seventeen \u2013 Boys Wish Encore Concert''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110336627|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc575\ucf5c\ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8\ub3c4 5\ubd84\ub9cc\uc5d0 \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4..\uce58\uc5f4|last=|first=|date=2016-01-19|website=Osen|publisher=|accessdate=January 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2016: Moderate success and first concert tour===\nSeventeen's first full-length studio album ''[[Love&Letter|Love & Letter]]'' was released on April 25, 2016. Besides success on domestic charts the album charted on the Oricon Weekly Pop Album Charts in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20160506n09471|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 'LOVE&LETTER' \u65e5\uc624\ub9ac\ucf58 \ud31d \uc568\ubc94 \ub7ad\ud0b9 1\uc704|last=|first=|date=2016-05-06|website=Nate News|publisher=|language=ko|accessdate=2016-09-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=18&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Seventeen received their first win on a music show with the album's lead single \"Pretty U\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201605042058269410|title=[\ud3ec\ud1a0\uc5d4]\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 '1\uc704 \uacf5\uc57d 2\uce35\uae4c\uc9c0\ub9cc \uc644\uc131\ub41c \uc778\uac04\ud0d1'(\uc1fc\ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8)|last=|first=|date=2016-05-04|website=Newsen|publisher=|language=ko|accessdate=May 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\n''Love & Letter'' was later re-released as a repackaged version on July 4 along with the lead single \"Very Nice\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newspim.com/news/view/20160613000310|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 7\uc6d4 \ucd08 \ub9ac\ud328\ud0a4\uc9c0 \uc568\ubc94\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31\u00b7\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \uc544\uc2dc\uc544 \ud22c\uc5b4\u20262016 '\ud2b9\uae09 \ub300\uc138\ub3cc' \uad73\ud788\uae30|last=|first=|date=2016-06-13|website=Newspim|publisher=|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201606151338322410|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uce21 \"\uc6d0\uc6b0 \uac74\uac15 \ubb38\uc81c\ub85c \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc911\ub2e8, 12\uc778 \uccb4\uc81c\ub85c..\"(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5 \uc804\ubb38)|last=|first=|date=2016-06-15|website=Newsen|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Promotions were immediately followed by Seventeen's ''1st Asia Tour 2016 Shining Diamonds'', which included venues in South Korea, Japan, Singapore, Australia, and China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen-17.com/asp/data_view.asp?board_seq=28534&parameter&board_code=1&types&search_val&page=1|title=[NOTICE] 2016 SEVENTEEN 1st Asia Tour: SHINING DIAMONDS \uc548\ub0b4\uacf5\uc9c0|website=Seventeen Official Website|accessdate=2016-05-15|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516172949/http://www.seventeen-17.com/asp/data_view.asp?board_seq=28534&parameter&board_code=1&types&search_val&page=1|archivedate=May 16, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000195425|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4..'\ub300\uc138\uc758 \uae38'|last=|first=|date=2016-06-25|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>\n\nOn December 5 the group released their third EP ''[[Going Seventeen]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.star.naver.com/SEVENTEEN/news/end?id=8534985|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 12\uc6d45\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815..\ubbf8\ub2c8\uc74c\ubc18 'GOING SEVENTEEN'|date=2016-11-21|website=OSEN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000933294|title=\ud655\uc2e4\ud558\uac8c \ub72c \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub354 \ub192\uc740 \uacf3\uc744 \ud5a5\ud574 '\ubd90\ubd90'|last=|first=|date=2016-12-26|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-12-17}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132018: Mainstream breakthrough and Commercial success===\n[[File:Seventeen performing Don't Wanna Cry at Dream Concert 2017 02.png|thumb|250px|right|Seventeen performing \"Don't Wanna Cry\" at Dream Concert 2017.]]\nSeventeen held six concerts in Japan between February 15\u201324 named ''17 Japan Concert: Say The Name #Seventeen''. The concerts attracted a total of 50,000 spectators despite the group not having officially debuted in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/music/now/read?oid=112&aid=0002896701|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u65e5 \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uc131\ub8cc\u2025\uad6d\ub0b4\uc678 \ub300\uc138\ub3cc \uc785\uc99d|accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref> On April 1, Seventeen became the first idol group to have a second season of the show ''One Fine Day'' after filming the series during their stay in Japan. The second season was titled ''One Fine Day in Japan'' and was created in collaboration between South Korean broadcaster [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] and Japanese network [[Music On! TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000241341|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc0ac\uc0c1 \ucd5c\ucd08 '\uc5b4\ub290 \uba4b\uc9c4 \ub0a0' \uc7ac\ucd9c\uc5f0...\uc77c\ubcf8\uc11c \uc0dd\uc874\ub825 \uac80\uc99d|accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=823297&_REFERER=http://news.naver.com/main/search/search.nhn?query=%25BC%25BC%25BA%25EC%25C6%25BE&ie=MS949|title=\uc5ec\uc11c\ub3c4\u2192\uc77c\ubcf8\u2026\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 '\uc5b4\ub290 \uba4b\uc9c4 \ub0a0' \ud55c\ubc88 \ub354 \ub5a0\ub09c\ub2e4|date=2017-02-24|accessdate=2017-04-05|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen's fourth EP ''[[Al1]]'' was released on May 22, 2017, which peaked at number one in Korea and has sold over 344,000 copies to date.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1205224|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 22\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0\u2026 2017\ub144 \uccab \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \uc601\uc0c1 \uae30\uc2b5 \uacf5\uac1c|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko}}</ref> A series of videos titled ''2017 Seventeen Project'' and three music videos subtitled ''Chapter 0.5 Before AL1'' were subsequently uploaded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2017091709493206838&VNA|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \ud0c0\uc784\ud14c\uc774\ube14 \uacf5\uac1c..\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc608\uace0|accessdate=2017-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1296483|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, '2017 SEVENTEEN PROJECT' \ud0c0\uc784 \ud14c\uc774\ube14 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110733593|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ud558\ubc18\uae30 \uc815\uaddc 2\uc9d1\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31..'\ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \ucc55\ud1303'|accessdate=2017-09-17}}</ref>\n\nThe group completed their first world tour, ''2017 Seventeen 1st World Tour \"Diamond Edge\"'', during which they visited thirteen cities in Asia and North America, on October 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen-17.com/mobile/asp/board_view.asp?board_seq=31790&board_code=1|title=[NOTICE] 2017 SEVENTEEN 1ST WORLD TOUR \"DIAMOND EDGE\" \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \uc548\ub0b4 [+ENG/JPN/CHN]|date=2017-05-13|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806020616/http://www.seventeen-17.com/mobile/asp/board_view.asp?board_seq=31790&board_code=1|archivedate=August 6, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn November 6, the group released their second full-length studio album ''[[Teen, Age]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1322328|title=\"\uc138\ube10\ud2f4\uc774 \uc628\ub2e4\"\u2026\ud504\ub85c\ubaa8\uc158 \ud0c0\uc784 \ud14c\uc774\ube14 \uacf5\uac1c|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen released a special album on February 5, 2018, named ''[[Director's Cut (Seventeen album)|Director's Cut]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201801200100155420011027&servicedate=20180119|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \"\uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \ub300\uc138 \uc785\uc99d\"...\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 2\uc6d4 5\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815|publisher=Sports Chosun|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110821212|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 2\uc6d4 5\uc77c \uac00\uc694\uacc4 \ucef4\ubc31\u2026'\ub514\ub809\ud130\uc2a4\ucef7' \uc2a4\ucf00\uc904 \uacf5\uac1c|publisher=Osen|language=ko}}</ref> Although ''Director's Cut'' contained all tracks from the previous ''Teen, Age'' album, it was promoted as a special album instead of a repackaged one due to the presence of four new tracks, including lead single \"Thanks\". The album has sold almost 600,000 copies to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/#!/home/SVCPost_394595979243520/detail|title=[Hi #\ubba4\uc9c1]\ucef4\ubc31 \uc55e\ub454 \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc65c '\uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc568\ubc94'\uc77c\uae4c|publisher=Star Hankook|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tvreport.co.kr/?c=news&m=newsview&idx=1035505|title=\ucef4\ubc31 D-8 \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc568\ubc94 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \ud3ec\ud1a0 \uacf5\uac1c [\uacf5\uc2dd]|publisher=Tvreport|language=ko}}</ref> \"Thanks\" reached first place on iTunes charts in 29 countries, including countries from North America, South America, Europe, and Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=22352996&cloc=|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 29\uac1c\uad6d 1\uc704 \uc5f0\uc77c \uae30\ub85d \uacbd\uc2e0\u2026\ud574\uc678\uc11c\ub3c4 \uc778\uc815\ud55c \uc568\ubc94|publisher=isplus|language=ko}}</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine named Seventeen one of the best K-pop groups during this promotion period.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/5124176/best-k-pop-artists/|title=These Are the Best K-Pop Groups You Should Know About|work=Time|first=Raisa|last=Bruner|date=February 9, 2018|accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen officially debuted in Japan on May 30 with their first Japanese mini-album ''We Make You''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=433&aid=0000041305|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u65e5 \ub370\ubdd4 \uae5c\uc9dd \ubc1c\ud45c\u2026\"5\uc6d4, \uac19\uc774 \uafc8 \uafc0\uae4c\uc694?\" (\uc694\ucf54\ud558\ub9c8)|publisher=Dispatch|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barks.jp/news/?id=1000154881|title=SEVENTEEN\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u66f2\u304c\u672c\u65e55/10\u306b\u521d\u30aa\u30f3\u30a8\u30a2|publisher=Barks}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen released their fifth EP ''You Make My Day'' on July 16. ''You Make My Day'' was their first release to be awarded with Platinum status.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=ALBUM|title=Gaon Certification \u2013 Album|website=Gaon Music Chart|accessdate=September 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.anewsa.com/detail.php?number=1347397&thread=07r05|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 5\uc9d1 \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \ucd08\ub3d9 27\ub9cc\uc7a5 \uae30\ub85d '\ud55c\ud130 \uc8fc\uac04 \ucc28\ud2b8 1\uc704'|publisher=Anewsa|language=ko}}</ref> Promotions for this album took place in between the ''Ideal Cut'' concerts in Seoul and concerts scheduled in other countries in Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=437888#08e1|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4(SVT), 16\uc77c \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 'YOU MAKE MY DAY' \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\uae5c\uc9dd \ucef4\ubc31 \uc18c\uc2dd \uc54c\ub824|publisher=Top Star News|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?year=2018&no=412959&refer=portal|title=\"\ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0 \uc774\uc5b4 \ub2ec\ub2ec \ud32c\uc0ac\ub791\"\u2026\uc138\ube10\ud2f4\uc758 \ub9d0\ub9d0\ub9d0|publisher=MBN Star|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: Continued success and ''An Ode''===\n\nSeventeen released their sixth EP [[You Made My Dawn#Track listing|''You Made My Dawn'']] on January 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=311&aid=0000939924|title= \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 21\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815\u2026\uc0c8\ud574 '\ub300\uc138' \ud589\ubcf4 \uc787\ub294\ub2e4|publisher=xsportsnews|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=609&aid=0000041545|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uce21 \"1\uc6d421\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815, \ub9c9\ubc14\uc9c0 \uc568\ubc94 \uc791\uc5c5\uc911\"(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5)|publisher=Newsen|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.joongdo.co.kr/main/view.php?key=20181231000745069|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 '\uc228\uc774 \ucc28' \uc548\ubb34 \uc601\uc0c1 \uae5c\uc9dd \uacf5\uac1c '\uce74\ub9ac\uc2a4\ub9c8+\ub0a8\uc131\ubbf8'|publisher=Joongdo|language=ko}}</ref> The title track \"Home\" is considered to be their most popular release yet, winning ten trophies on weekly music shows. The EP also attained two ''triple crowns'' which consist of three consecutive wins on any one weekly music show, and a ''grand slam'' which consists of winning trophies on [[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]], [[Inkigayo]], [[M Countdown]], [[Show! Music Core]], and [[Show Champion]] in a single promotion period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.mk.co.kr/view.php?year=2019&no=92921|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u2018HOME\u2019 \ud65c\ub3d9 \ub9c8\uce68\ud45c \"1\uc704 9\uad00\uc655\uc740 \uce90\ub7ff \uc751\uc6d0 \ub355\ubd84\"|publisher=MKSports|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1077125|title=\n'\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c' \uc6b0\ub514VS\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub098\ub780\ud788 1\uc704 \ud6c4\ubcf4\u2026\uc2b9\uc790\ub294|publisher=Xsportsnews|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nOn May 29, Seventeen released their first Japanese single \"Happy Ending\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201905301424153732432_1|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u65e5\uc2f1\uae00 'Happy Ending' \ub370\uc77c\ub9ac \uc74c\ubc18 \ud310\ub9e4\ub7c9 11\ub9cc\uc7a5 \ub3cc\ud30c[\uacf5\uc2dd]|publisher=Herald News|language=ko}}</ref> which peaked at #1 on the Oricon Daily Singles Chart<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.psnews.co.kr/news/article.html?no=41649|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 'Happy Ending' \ub610\ud55c \ud574\uc678 \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 \ucc28\ud2b8\uc5d0 \uc11c\ub3c4 \uc77c\ubc88...|publisher=PSnews|language=ko}}</ref> and went on to receive Platinum status from [[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaj.or.jp/f/data/cert/gd.html |title=\u6708\u6b21\u8a8d\u5b9a\u4f5c\u54c1\u3000\u8a8d\u5b9a\u5e74\u6708\uff1a2018\u5e74 11\u6708 -  \u6d0b\u697d \u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0|website=www.riaj.or.jp |language=ja |accessdate=June 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 5, Seventeen released the digital single \"Hit\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nspna.com/news/?mode=view&newsid=374022|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 8\uc6d4 5\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31..\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \ud65c\ub3d9 \ud3ec\ubb38|publisher=NSP News|language=ko}}</ref> The single was a precursor to the group's third studio album ''[[An Ode#Track listing|An Ode]]'', which was released on September 16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/265353|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u7f8e \ube4c\ubcf4\ub4dc\uc11c \ub2e8\ub3c5 \uc778\ud130\ubdf0! \uc5ec\uc804\ud788 \ub728\uac70\uc6b4 \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c\uc801\uc778 \uad00\uc2ec|publisher=iMBC|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportsseoul.com/news/read/807230|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ucef4\ubc31 \uc900\ube44\u2026\ubb34\ub354\uc704 \ub0a0\ub9b4 \uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \uc12c\uba38 \uc1a1 BEST 3|publisher=Sports Seoul}}</ref> ''An Ode'' is the group's best-selling album to date, selling over 700,000 copies in its first week<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=673068|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4(SVT) \uc815\uaddc 3\uc9d1 'An Ode', \ucd08\ub3d9 \uc9d1\uacc4 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9\ub0a0 \uadf9\uc801 70\ub9cc\uc7a5 \ub3cc\ud30c\u2026\uc5ed\ub300 \ubcf4\uc774\uadf8\ub8f9 6\uc704 \uae30\ub85d \ub2ec\uc131|publisher=Top Star News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2019&termGbn=month|title=2019\ub144 9\uc6d4  Album Chart|website=Gaon Music Chart|language=ko}}</ref> and granting the group's first ''daesang'' or grand prize for Album of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019112208370213152|title=\uc288\uc8fc\u00b7\uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8\u00b7\ud2b8\uc640\uc774\uc2a4\u00b7\uc138\ube10\ud2f4..'AAA'\uc640 \ub2e4\uc2dc \ud55c\ubc88!\u2461 [2019 AAA in \ubca0\ud2b8\ub0a8]|publisher= Star News}}</ref> It was also critically acclaimed as the best K-pop album of the year by [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8547186/the-25-best-k-pop-albums-of-2019-critics-picks|title=The 25 Best K-pop Albums of 2019: Critics' Picks|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n\nOn April 1, 2020 Seventeen released their second Japanese single \"Fallin' Flower\", which sold more than 400,000 copies in its first week and secured first place on [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]'s Japan Hot 100 Chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/9354426/seventeen-fallin-flower-gen-hoshino-social-media-dancing-on-the-inside-japan-hot-100-chart|title=SEVENTEEN Debuts at No. 1 on Japan Hot 100|date=2020-04-08|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n\n===Hip-hop unit===\n* S.Coups ({{Korean|\uc5d0\uc2a4\ucff1\uc2a4}}) \u2014 group leader, hip-hop unit leader\n* Wonwoo ({{Korean|\uc6d0\uc6b0|labels=no}})\n* Mingyu ({{Korean|\ubbfc\uaddc|labels=no}})\n* Vernon ({{Korean|\ubc84\ub17c|labels=no}})\n\n===Vocal unit===\n* Jeonghan ({{Korean|\uc815\ud55c|labels=no}})\n* Joshua ({{Korean|\uc870\uc288\uc544|labels=no}})\n* Woozi ({{Korean|\uc6b0\uc9c0|labels=no}}) \u2014 vocal unit leader\n* DK {{small|(also known as Dokyeom)}} ({{Korean|\ub3c4\uacb8|labels=no}})\n* [[Seungkwan]] ({{Korean|\uc2b9\uad00|labels=no}})\n\n===Performance unit===\n* [[Wen Junhui|Jun]] ({{Korean|\uc900|labels=no}})\n* Hoshi ({{Korean|\ud638\uc2dc|labels=no}}) \u2014 performance unit leader\n* [[The8]] ({{Korean|\ub514\uc5d0\uc787|labels=no}})\n* Dino ({{Korean|\ub514\ub178|labels=no}})\n\n=== Original Members / Ex-Members<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seventeen_TV|title=Seventeen TV|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> ===\n\n* [[Jang Do-yoon|Jang Doyoon]] (\uc7a5\ub3c4\uc724)\n* Yao Mingming (\u59da\u660e\u660e)\n* Shin Dongjin (\uc2e0\ub3d9\uc9c4)\n* [[Samuel (singer)|Kim Samuel]] (\uae40\uc0ac\ubb34\uc5d8)\n\n==Subgroups==\n===Seventeen BSS===\nOn March 21, 2018, members Seungkwan, DK, and Hoshi debuted as a subgroup called ''BSS'' or ''BooSeokSoon'', a common nickname for the three members together. The group released their debut single \"Just Do It\" and enjoyed a short promotion period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003735810|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uccab \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc720\ub2db '\ubd80\uc11d\uc21c' \ucd9c\uaca9\u20263\uc6d4 \uc2e0\uace1\ubc1c\ud45c|publisher=Osen|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=011&aid=0003242839|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uce21 \"\ud638\uc2dcX\uc2b9\uad00X\ub3c4\uacb8, \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc720\ub2db 3\uc6d4 \uacf5\uac1c\"|publisher=\uc11c\uacbd\uc2a4\ud0c0|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Seventeen discography}}\n* ''[[Love & Letter]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Teen, Age]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[An Ode]]'' (2019)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Network\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n| ''Big Debut Plan''<ref name=\"naver1\"/>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016\n| ''Seventeen's One Fine Day''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mbcplus.com/seventeenday|title=Seventeenday|accessdate=2017-02-26|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422114328/http://www.mbcplus.com/seventeenday|archivedate=April 22, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2017\n| ''Seventeen's One Fine Day in Japan''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000241341|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc0ac\uc0c1 \ucd5c\ucd08 '\uc5b4\ub290 \uba4b\uc9c4 \ub0a0' \uc7ac\ucd9c\uc5f0...\uc77c\ubcf8\uc11c \uc0dd\uc874\ub825 \uac80\uc99d|last=|first=|date=2016-12-26|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2017-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2018\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[M.net|Mnet]]\n|''SVT Club''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000832712|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc0c8 \ub9ac\uc5bc\ub9ac\ud2f0 'SVT\ud074\ub7fd' \uc120\ubcf4\uc778\ub2e4\u2026\u97d3\u00b7\u65e5 \ub3d9\uc2dc \ubc29\uc1a1|last=|first=|date=2018-03-12|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2018-03-14}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Concerts and tours==\n{{Main|List of Seventeen concert tours}}\n\n===Headlining===\n\n====Asia tours====\n* Seventeen 1st Asia Tour 2016 Shining Diamonds (2016)\n* Ideal Cut (2018)\n\n====World tours====\n* Seventeen 1st World Tour Diamond Edge (2017)\n* Ideal Cut (2018)\n* Ode to You (2019-2020)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Seventeen}}\n\nSeventeen earned three rookie awards in their debut year, and have since earned six 'bonsangs,' which are main prizes, and one 'daesang' or grand prize.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1RUKEGHYFL|title=[2018 \uc11c\uac00\ub300] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \ubcf8\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1, \"\uc791\ub144\uc5d0 \ubc1b\uc740 \uc0ac\ub791 \uc62c\ud574 \uaf2d \ubcf4\ub2f5\ud560 \uac83\"|accessdate=2018-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?year=2018&no=25590&refer=portal|title=[2018 \uace8\ub4e0\ub514\uc2a4\ud06c] '\ubcf8\uc0c1' \ud669\uce58\uc5f4\u00b7\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \"\uc874\uc7ac\uc758 \uc774\uc720=\ud32c, \uc9c4\uc2ec\uc73c\ub85c \uac10\uc0ac\"|accessdate=2018-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019112208370213152|title=\uc288\uc8fc\u00b7\uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8\u00b7\ud2b8\uc640\uc774\uc2a4\u00b7\uc138\ube10\ud2f4..'AAA'\uc640 \ub2e4\uc2dc \ud55c\ubc88!\u2461 [2019 AAA in \ubca0\ud2b8\ub0a8]|accessdate=2019-11-26}}</ref> They have also gained several awards for choreography and dance performance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1111049515|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ud64d\ucf69 \uc9d1\uc5b4\uc0bc\ud0a8 \uc2e0\uace1 \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4\u2026\ub3c5\ubcf4\uc801 \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 '\uc228\uc774 \ucc28'|accessdate=2018-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?year=2017&no=792680&refer=portal|title=[2017 MAMA] \ubca0\uc2a4\ud2b8 \ub304\uc2a4 \ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4 \uadf8\ub8f9\uc0c1 \uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \"'\uc790\uccb4 \uc81c\uc791\ub3cc' \uba85\uc608 \uc9c0\ucf1c\"|accessdate=2018-12-15}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Commons category|Seventeen (South Korean band)|Seventeen}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.pledis.co.kr/html/artist/seventeen}}\n\n{{Seventeen (band)}}\n{{Pledis Entertainment}}\n{{Golden Disk Awards for New Artist of the Year}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Seventeen (South Korean band)| ]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop music groups]]\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:South Korean boy bands]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Pledis Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:Mnet Asian Music Award winners]]\n[[Category:Melon Music Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean boy group}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Seventeen\n| background      = group_or_band\n| image           = 180716 Seveteen performing \"Oh My!\" at You Make My Day Showcase.png\n| image_size      =\n| landscape       = yes\n| alt             = \n| caption         = Seventeen performing \"Oh My!\" in July 2018<br />Top row: Woozi, Wonwoo, Vernon, Mingyu, [[Wen Junhui|Jun]], Hoshi, [[The8]], and DK<br />Bottom row: Joshua, Jeonghan, Dino, S.Coups, and [[Seungkwan]] \n| alias           = \n| origin          = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[K-pop]]\n* [[synthpop]]\n* [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| years_active    = {{start date|2015}}\u2013present\n| label           = Pledis Entertainment\n| associated_acts = [[Bumzu]], BooSeokSoon\n| website         = {{url|http://www.pledis.co.kr/html/artist/seventeen|Korean Website}}<br />{{url|https://seventeen-17.jp/|Japanese Website}}\n| current_members = \n*S.Coups\n*Jeonghan\n*Joshua\n*[[Wen Junhui|Jun]]\n*Hoshi\n*Wonwoo\n*Woozi\n*DK\n*Mingyu\n*[[The8]]\n*[[Seungkwan]]\n*Vernon\n*Dino\n}}\n'''Seventeen''' ({{Korean|hangul=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4}}), also stylized as '''SEVENTEEN''' or '''SVT''', is a South Korean boy band formed by [[Pledis Entertainment]] in 2015. The group consists of 13 members divided into three sub-units, each with a different area of specialization: 'Hip-Hop Unit', 'Vocal Unit', and 'Performance Unit'. Seventeen has released three studio albums and six extended plays.\n\nSeventeen is considered a \"self-producing\" [[Korean pop idol|idol group]], with the members being actively involved in the songwriting, choreographing, and other aspects of the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20150526000750|title=Seventeen hopes to shine like diamonds with '17 Carat'|date=2015-05-26|website=The Korea Herald|accessdate=2016-05-09}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7356946/seventeen-first-loveletter-album-world-heatseekers-charts|title=Seventeen Send Their 'First Love&Letter' to Top 5 of World & Heatseekers Album Charts|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2016-05-04|website=Billboard|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n===2013\u20132015: Formation and early years===\n\n====''Seventeen TV''====\n{{Main|Seventeen TV}}\nStarting in 2013, Seventeen appeared in regular live broadcasts of a show called ''Seventeen TV'' on the online streaming platform [[UStream]]. The show had multiple seasons in which the trainees were introduced and shown practicing performances, with some seasons ending in ''Like Seventeen'' concerts.<ref>{{cite news|work=HEI|language=korean|url=http://hei.hankyung.com/hub02/201311263531q|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uc138 \ubc88\uc9f8 \ucf58\uc2a4\ud2b8, \ub2e4\uc591\ud55c \ubb34\ub300\ub85c \ud32c\ub4e4 \ub9e4\ub8cc|trans-title= Seventeen's third concert, captivated fans with various stages|date=November 23, 2013|accessdate=March 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|work=OSEN|language=korean|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109927555|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub370\ubdd4\uc804 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uc5f0\ub2e4..'\ucd5c\uc885 \uc810\uac80' |trans-title=Seventeen, last concert before debut revealed...'the final check'|date=August 12, 2014|accessdate=March 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====''Big Debut Plan''====\nPrior to debut, Seventeen also appeared in the reality TV show ''Seventeen Project: Big Debut Plan'', broadcast on [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] between May 2\u201326, 2015. The show concluded with the group's debut showcase.<ref name=\"naver1\">{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000466732|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8' \uccab \ubc29\uc1a1\u202613\u8272 \ub9e4\ub825 \ub2f4\uc558\ub2e4 '\ub9ac\uc5bc+\uc5f4\uc815'|last=|first=|date=2015-05-02|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-31}}</ref>\n\n====''Debut''====\n[[File:Seventeen (\uc138\ube10\ud2f4) at 2015 Summer K-POP Festival.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Seventeen performing at the 2015 Summer K-POP Festival at the [[Seoul Plaza]].]]\nSeventeen debuted on May 26 with a live showcase televised by MBC. They were the first male K-pop group to debut with a one-hour live showcase on a major broadcasting channel, with label-mates [[Lizzy (singer)|Lizzy]] and [[Raina (singer)|Raina]] serving as [[Master of ceremonies|MC]]<nowiki/>s.<ref name=\"The Korea Herald\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20150526000750|title=Seventeen hopes to shine like diamonds with '17 Carat'|last=Won|first=Ho-jung|date=2015-05-26|website=The Korea Herald|publisher=|accessdate=June 21, 2015}}</ref> Three days later, their first EP ''[[17 Carat]]'' was digitally released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6582987/seventeen-adore-u-13-member-boy-band|title=Here's What a 13-Member K-Pop Boy Band Looks Like: Watch 'Adore U' by Seventeen|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2015-05-30|website=Billboard|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-15}}</ref> ''17 Carat'' became the longest-charting K-pop album of the year in the US<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2015/12/kpop-debuts-rookies-best#1|title=K-Pop's 2015 Rookies: Who's Working It, & Who Needs Work|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2015-12-22|website=Fuse|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-15}}</ref> and was the only rookie album to appear on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s \"10 Best K-Pop Albums of 2015\" chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6828137/best-k-pop-albums-2015|title=The 10 Best K-Pop Albums of 2015|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|last2=Oak|first2=Jessica|date=2015-12-30|website=Billboard|publisher=|accessdate=January 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/101572/seventeen-is-only-rookie-group-to-make-billboards-best-k-pop-albums-list|title=KPOP NEWS \u2013 Seventeen is Only Rookie Group to Make Billboard\u2032s Best K-Pop Albums List {{!}} Mwave|last=Kim|first=JiYeon|date=2016-01-16|website=Mwave|publisher=|accessdate=2016-05-09}}</ref>\n\nOn September 10 their second EP ''[[Boys Be (EP)|Boys Be]]'' was released, which would later become the highest selling rookie album of 2015.<ref name=\"2015\ub144 38\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart\">{{cite web | title = 2015\ub144 38\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart | author =  | publisher = [[Gaon Chart]] | date =  | accessdate = September 22, 2015 | url = http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=38&hitYear=2015&termGbn=week | language = ko }}</ref> The album's success earned the group awards at the [[Golden Disk Awards]], [[Seoul Music Awards]], and [[Gaon Chart K-Pop Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.sg/seventeen-return-brand-new-album-1918|title=Seventeen to return with a brand new album|last=Kaur|first=Gunjeet|date=2016-06-15|website=International Business Times|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003240481|title=\uc544\uc774\ucf58\u00b7\uc138\ube10\ud2f4\u00b7\uc5ec\uc790\uce5c\uad6c, \uc2e0\uc778\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1 [25th \uc11c\uc6b8\uac00\uc694\ub300\uc0c1]|last=|first=|date=2016-01-14|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Seventeen was also the only K-pop group on [[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'s \"21 Under 21 2015: Music's Hottest Young Stars\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=404&aid=0000118634|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, '\ube4c\ubcf4\ub4dc 21 Under 21' \uc544\uc2dc\uc544 \uac00\uc218 \uc720\uc77c \uc120\uc815|last=|first=|date=2015-11-01|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/photos/6745079/billboard-21-under-21-2015-hottest-young-stars/6|title=Billboard's 21 Under 21 2015: Music's Hottest Young Stars|last=Partridge|first=Kenneth|date=2015-10-30|website=Billboard|publisher=|accessdate=October 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen held a four-date concert series titled ''2015 Like Seventeen \u2013 Boys Wish'' from the 24th to the 26th of December as an end-of-year celebration in Seoul.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003208833|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uccab \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8, \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508 1\ubd84 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub9e4\uc9c4..'\uae30\uc5fc'|last=|first=|date=2015-11-24|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> After the concerts' success, Seventeen held two related concerts the following February in 2016, entitled ''Like Seventeen \u2013 Boys Wish Encore Concert''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110336627|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc575\ucf5c\ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8\ub3c4 5\ubd84\ub9cc\uc5d0 \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4..\uce58\uc5f4|last=|first=|date=2016-01-19|website=Osen|publisher=|accessdate=January 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2016: Moderate success and first concert tour===\nSeventeen's first full-length studio album ''[[Love&Letter|Love & Letter]]'' was released on April 25, 2016. Besides success on domestic charts the album charted on the Oricon Weekly Pop Album Charts in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20160506n09471|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 'LOVE&LETTER' \u65e5\uc624\ub9ac\ucf58 \ud31d \uc568\ubc94 \ub7ad\ud0b9 1\uc704|last=|first=|date=2016-05-06|website=Nate News|publisher=|language=ko|accessdate=2016-09-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=18&hitYear=2016&termGbn=week|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Seventeen received their first win on a music show with the album's lead single \"Pretty U\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201605042058269410|title=[\ud3ec\ud1a0\uc5d4]\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 '1\uc704 \uacf5\uc57d 2\uce35\uae4c\uc9c0\ub9cc \uc644\uc131\ub41c \uc778\uac04\ud0d1'(\uc1fc\ucc54\ud53c\uc5b8)|last=|first=|date=2016-05-04|website=Newsen|publisher=|language=ko|accessdate=May 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\n''Love & Letter'' was later re-released as a repackaged version on July 4 along with the lead single \"Very Nice\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newspim.com/news/view/20160613000310|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 7\uc6d4 \ucd08 \ub9ac\ud328\ud0a4\uc9c0 \uc568\ubc94\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31\u00b7\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \uc544\uc2dc\uc544 \ud22c\uc5b4\u20262016 '\ud2b9\uae09 \ub300\uc138\ub3cc' \uad73\ud788\uae30|last=|first=|date=2016-06-13|website=Newspim|publisher=|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201606151338322410|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uce21 \"\uc6d0\uc6b0 \uac74\uac15 \ubb38\uc81c\ub85c \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc911\ub2e8, 12\uc778 \uccb4\uc81c\ub85c..\"(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5 \uc804\ubb38)|last=|first=|date=2016-06-15|website=Newsen|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Promotions were immediately followed by Seventeen's ''1st Asia Tour 2016 Shining Diamonds'', which included venues in South Korea, Japan, Singapore, Australia, and China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen-17.com/asp/data_view.asp?board_seq=28534&parameter&board_code=1&types&search_val&page=1|title=[NOTICE] 2016 SEVENTEEN 1st Asia Tour: SHINING DIAMONDS \uc548\ub0b4\uacf5\uc9c0|website=Seventeen Official Website|accessdate=2016-05-15|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516172949/http://www.seventeen-17.com/asp/data_view.asp?board_seq=28534&parameter&board_code=1&types&search_val&page=1|archivedate=May 16, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000195425|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4..'\ub300\uc138\uc758 \uae38'|last=|first=|date=2016-06-25|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>\n\nOn December 5 the group released their third EP ''[[Going Seventeen]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.star.naver.com/SEVENTEEN/news/end?id=8534985|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 12\uc6d45\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815..\ubbf8\ub2c8\uc74c\ubc18 'GOING SEVENTEEN'|date=2016-11-21|website=OSEN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000933294|title=\ud655\uc2e4\ud558\uac8c \ub72c \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub354 \ub192\uc740 \uacf3\uc744 \ud5a5\ud574 '\ubd90\ubd90'|last=|first=|date=2016-12-26|website=Naver News|publisher=|accessdate=2016-12-17}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132018: Mainstream breakthrough and Commercial success===\n[[File:Seventeen performing Don't Wanna Cry at Dream Concert 2017 02.png|thumb|250px|right|Seventeen performing \"Don't Wanna Cry\" at Dream Concert 2017.]]\nSeventeen held six concerts in Japan between February 15\u201324 named ''17 Japan Concert: Say The Name #Seventeen''. The concerts attracted a total of 50,000 spectators despite the group not having officially debuted in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/music/now/read?oid=112&aid=0002896701|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u65e5 \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uc131\ub8cc\u2025\uad6d\ub0b4\uc678 \ub300\uc138\ub3cc \uc785\uc99d|accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref> On April 1, Seventeen became the first idol group to have a second season of the show ''One Fine Day'' after filming the series during their stay in Japan. The second season was titled ''One Fine Day in Japan'' and was created in collaboration between South Korean broadcaster [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] and Japanese network [[Music On! TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000241341|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc0ac\uc0c1 \ucd5c\ucd08 '\uc5b4\ub290 \uba4b\uc9c4 \ub0a0' \uc7ac\ucd9c\uc5f0...\uc77c\ubcf8\uc11c \uc0dd\uc874\ub825 \uac80\uc99d|accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=823297&_REFERER=http://news.naver.com/main/search/search.nhn?query=%25BC%25BC%25BA%25EC%25C6%25BE&ie=MS949|title=\uc5ec\uc11c\ub3c4\u2192\uc77c\ubcf8\u2026\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 '\uc5b4\ub290 \uba4b\uc9c4 \ub0a0' \ud55c\ubc88 \ub354 \ub5a0\ub09c\ub2e4|date=2017-02-24|accessdate=2017-04-05|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen's fourth EP ''[[Al1]]'' was released on May 22, 2017, which peaked at number one in Korea and has sold over 344,000 copies to date.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1205224|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 22\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0\u2026 2017\ub144 \uccab \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \uc601\uc0c1 \uae30\uc2b5 \uacf5\uac1c|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko}}</ref> A series of videos titled ''2017 Seventeen Project'' and three music videos subtitled ''Chapter 0.5 Before AL1'' were subsequently uploaded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2017091709493206838&VNA|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \ud0c0\uc784\ud14c\uc774\ube14 \uacf5\uac1c..\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc608\uace0|accessdate=2017-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1296483|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, '2017 SEVENTEEN PROJECT' \ud0c0\uc784 \ud14c\uc774\ube14 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110733593|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ud558\ubc18\uae30 \uc815\uaddc 2\uc9d1\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31..'\ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \ucc55\ud1303'|accessdate=2017-09-17}}</ref>\n\nThe group completed their first world tour, ''2017 Seventeen 1st World Tour \"Diamond Edge\"'', during which they visited thirteen cities in Asia and North America, on October 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen-17.com/mobile/asp/board_view.asp?board_seq=31790&board_code=1|title=[NOTICE] 2017 SEVENTEEN 1ST WORLD TOUR \"DIAMOND EDGE\" \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \uc548\ub0b4 [+ENG/JPN/CHN]|date=2017-05-13|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806020616/http://www.seventeen-17.com/mobile/asp/board_view.asp?board_seq=31790&board_code=1|archivedate=August 6, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn November 6, the group released their second full-length studio album ''[[Teen, Age]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1322328|title=\"\uc138\ube10\ud2f4\uc774 \uc628\ub2e4\"\u2026\ud504\ub85c\ubaa8\uc158 \ud0c0\uc784 \ud14c\uc774\ube14 \uacf5\uac1c|publisher=Ten Asia|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen released a special album on February 5, 2018, named ''[[Director's Cut (Seventeen album)|Director's Cut]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201801200100155420011027&servicedate=20180119|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \"\uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \ub300\uc138 \uc785\uc99d\"...\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 2\uc6d4 5\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815|publisher=Sports Chosun|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110821212|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 2\uc6d4 5\uc77c \uac00\uc694\uacc4 \ucef4\ubc31\u2026'\ub514\ub809\ud130\uc2a4\ucef7' \uc2a4\ucf00\uc904 \uacf5\uac1c|publisher=Osen|language=ko}}</ref> Although ''Director's Cut'' contained all tracks from the previous ''Teen, Age'' album, it was promoted as a special album instead of a repackaged one due to the presence of four new tracks, including lead single \"Thanks\". The album has sold almost 600,000 copies to date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/#!/home/SVCPost_394595979243520/detail|title=[Hi #\ubba4\uc9c1]\ucef4\ubc31 \uc55e\ub454 \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc65c '\uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc568\ubc94'\uc77c\uae4c|publisher=Star Hankook|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tvreport.co.kr/?c=news&m=newsview&idx=1035505|title=\ucef4\ubc31 D-8 \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc568\ubc94 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \ud3ec\ud1a0 \uacf5\uac1c [\uacf5\uc2dd]|publisher=Tvreport|language=ko}}</ref> \"Thanks\" reached first place on iTunes charts in 29 countries, including countries from North America, South America, Europe, and Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=22352996&cloc=|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 29\uac1c\uad6d 1\uc704 \uc5f0\uc77c \uae30\ub85d \uacbd\uc2e0\u2026\ud574\uc678\uc11c\ub3c4 \uc778\uc815\ud55c \uc568\ubc94|publisher=isplus|language=ko}}</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine named Seventeen one of the best K-pop groups during this promotion period.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/5124176/best-k-pop-artists/|title=These Are the Best K-Pop Groups You Should Know About|work=Time|first=Raisa|last=Bruner|date=February 9, 2018|accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen officially debuted in Japan on May 30 with their first Japanese mini-album ''We Make You''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=433&aid=0000041305|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u65e5 \ub370\ubdd4 \uae5c\uc9dd \ubc1c\ud45c\u2026\"5\uc6d4, \uac19\uc774 \uafc8 \uafc0\uae4c\uc694?\" (\uc694\ucf54\ud558\ub9c8)|publisher=Dispatch|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barks.jp/news/?id=1000154881|title=SEVENTEEN\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u66f2\u304c\u672c\u65e55/10\u306b\u521d\u30aa\u30f3\u30a8\u30a2|publisher=Barks}}</ref>\n\nSeventeen released their fifth EP ''You Make My Day'' on July 16. ''You Make My Day'' was their first release to be awarded with Platinum status.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=ALBUM|title=Gaon Certification \u2013 Album|website=Gaon Music Chart|accessdate=September 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.anewsa.com/detail.php?number=1347397&thread=07r05|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 5\uc9d1 \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \ucd08\ub3d9 27\ub9cc\uc7a5 \uae30\ub85d '\ud55c\ud130 \uc8fc\uac04 \ucc28\ud2b8 1\uc704'|publisher=Anewsa|language=ko}}</ref> Promotions for this album took place in between the ''Ideal Cut'' concerts in Seoul and concerts scheduled in other countries in Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=437888#08e1|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4(SVT), 16\uc77c \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 'YOU MAKE MY DAY' \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\uae5c\uc9dd \ucef4\ubc31 \uc18c\uc2dd \uc54c\ub824|publisher=Top Star News|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?year=2018&no=412959&refer=portal|title=\"\ucef4\ubc31 \uc608\uace0 \uc774\uc5b4 \ub2ec\ub2ec \ud32c\uc0ac\ub791\"\u2026\uc138\ube10\ud2f4\uc758 \ub9d0\ub9d0\ub9d0|publisher=MBN Star|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: Continued success and ''An Ode''===\n\nSeventeen released their sixth EP [[You Made My Dawn#Track listing|''You Made My Dawn'']] on January 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=311&aid=0000939924|title= \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 21\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815\u2026\uc0c8\ud574 '\ub300\uc138' \ud589\ubcf4 \uc787\ub294\ub2e4|publisher=xsportsnews|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=609&aid=0000041545|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uce21 \"1\uc6d421\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815, \ub9c9\ubc14\uc9c0 \uc568\ubc94 \uc791\uc5c5\uc911\"(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5)|publisher=Newsen|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.joongdo.co.kr/main/view.php?key=20181231000745069|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4 '\uc228\uc774 \ucc28' \uc548\ubb34 \uc601\uc0c1 \uae5c\uc9dd \uacf5\uac1c '\uce74\ub9ac\uc2a4\ub9c8+\ub0a8\uc131\ubbf8'|publisher=Joongdo|language=ko}}</ref> The title track \"Home\" is considered to be their most popular release yet, winning ten trophies on weekly music shows. The EP also attained two ''triple crowns'' which consist of three consecutive wins on any one weekly music show, and a ''grand slam'' which consists of winning trophies on [[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]], [[Inkigayo]], [[M Countdown]], [[Show! Music Core]], and [[Show Champion]] in a single promotion period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.mk.co.kr/view.php?year=2019&no=92921|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u2018HOME\u2019 \ud65c\ub3d9 \ub9c8\uce68\ud45c \"1\uc704 9\uad00\uc655\uc740 \uce90\ub7ff \uc751\uc6d0 \ub355\ubd84\"|publisher=MKSports|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1077125|title=\n'\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c' \uc6b0\ub514VS\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ub098\ub780\ud788 1\uc704 \ud6c4\ubcf4\u2026\uc2b9\uc790\ub294|publisher=Xsportsnews|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nOn May 29, Seventeen released their first Japanese single \"Happy Ending\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201905301424153732432_1|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u65e5\uc2f1\uae00 'Happy Ending' \ub370\uc77c\ub9ac \uc74c\ubc18 \ud310\ub9e4\ub7c9 11\ub9cc\uc7a5 \ub3cc\ud30c[\uacf5\uc2dd]|publisher=Herald News|language=ko}}</ref> which peaked at #1 on the Oricon Daily Singles Chart<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.psnews.co.kr/news/article.html?no=41649|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 'Happy Ending' \ub610\ud55c \ud574\uc678 \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 \ucc28\ud2b8\uc5d0 \uc11c\ub3c4 \uc77c\ubc88...|publisher=PSnews|language=ko}}</ref> and went on to receive Platinum status from [[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaj.or.jp/f/data/cert/gd.html |title=\u6708\u6b21\u8a8d\u5b9a\u4f5c\u54c1\u3000\u8a8d\u5b9a\u5e74\u6708\uff1a2018\u5e74 11\u6708 -  \u6d0b\u697d \u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0|website=www.riaj.or.jp |language=ja |accessdate=June 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 5, Seventeen released the digital single \"Hit\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nspna.com/news/?mode=view&newsid=374022|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, 8\uc6d4 5\uc77c \ucef4\ubc31..\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \ud65c\ub3d9 \ud3ec\ubb38|publisher=NSP News|language=ko}}</ref> The single was a precursor to the group's third studio album ''[[An Ode#Track listing|An Ode]]'', which was released on September 16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/265353|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \u7f8e \ube4c\ubcf4\ub4dc\uc11c \ub2e8\ub3c5 \uc778\ud130\ubdf0! \uc5ec\uc804\ud788 \ub728\uac70\uc6b4 \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c\uc801\uc778 \uad00\uc2ec|publisher=iMBC|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportsseoul.com/news/read/807230|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \ucef4\ubc31 \uc900\ube44\u2026\ubb34\ub354\uc704 \ub0a0\ub9b4 \uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \uc12c\uba38 \uc1a1 BEST 3|publisher=Sports Seoul}}</ref> ''An Ode'' is the group's best-selling album to date, selling over 700,000 copies in its first week<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=673068|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4(SVT) \uc815\uaddc 3\uc9d1 'An Ode', \ucd08\ub3d9 \uc9d1\uacc4 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9\ub0a0 \uadf9\uc801 70\ub9cc\uc7a5 \ub3cc\ud30c\u2026\uc5ed\ub300 \ubcf4\uc774\uadf8\ub8f9 6\uc704 \uae30\ub85d \ub2ec\uc131|publisher=Top Star News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2019&termGbn=month|title=2019\ub144 9\uc6d4  Album Chart|website=Gaon Music Chart|language=ko}}</ref> and granting the group's first ''daesang'' or grand prize for Album of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019112208370213152|title=\uc288\uc8fc\u00b7\uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8\u00b7\ud2b8\uc640\uc774\uc2a4\u00b7\uc138\ube10\ud2f4..'AAA'\uc640 \ub2e4\uc2dc \ud55c\ubc88!\u2461 [2019 AAA in \ubca0\ud2b8\ub0a8]|publisher= Star News}}</ref> It was also critically acclaimed as the best K-pop album of the year by [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8547186/the-25-best-k-pop-albums-of-2019-critics-picks|title=The 25 Best K-pop Albums of 2019: Critics' Picks|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n\nOn April 1, 2020 Seventeen released their second Japanese single \"Fallin' Flower\", which sold more than 400,000 copies in its first week and secured first place on [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]'s Japan Hot 100 Chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/9354426/seventeen-fallin-flower-gen-hoshino-social-media-dancing-on-the-inside-japan-hot-100-chart|title=SEVENTEEN Debuts at No. 1 on Japan Hot 100|date=2020-04-08|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n\n===Hip-hop unit===\n* S.Coups ({{Korean|\uc5d0\uc2a4\ucff1\uc2a4}}) \u2014 group leader, hip-hop unit leader\n* Wonwoo ({{Korean|\uc6d0\uc6b0|labels=no}})\n* Mingyu ({{Korean|\ubbfc\uaddc|labels=no}})\n* Vernon ({{Korean|\ubc84\ub17c|labels=no}})\n\n===Vocal unit===\n* Jeonghan ({{Korean|\uc815\ud55c|labels=no}})\n* Joshua ({{Korean|\uc870\uc288\uc544|labels=no}})\n* Woozi ({{Korean|\uc6b0\uc9c0|labels=no}}) \u2014 vocal unit leader\n* DK {{small|(also known as Dokyeom)}} ({{Korean|\ub3c4\uacb8|labels=no}})\n* [[Seungkwan]] ({{Korean|\uc2b9\uad00|labels=no}})\n\n===Performance unit===\n* [[Wen Junhui|Jun]] ({{Korean|\uc900|labels=no}})\n* Hoshi ({{Korean|\ud638\uc2dc|labels=no}}) \u2014 performance unit leader\n* [[The8]] ({{Korean|\ub514\uc5d0\uc787|labels=no}})\n* Dino ({{Korean|\ub514\ub178|labels=no}})\n\n==Subgroups==\n===Seventeen BSS===\nOn March 21, 2018, members Seungkwan, DK, and Hoshi debuted as a subgroup called ''BSS'' or ''BooSeokSoon'', a common nickname for the three members together. The group released their debut single \"Just Do It\" and enjoyed a short promotion period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003735810|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uccab \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc720\ub2db '\ubd80\uc11d\uc21c' \ucd9c\uaca9\u20263\uc6d4 \uc2e0\uace1\ubc1c\ud45c|publisher=Osen|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=011&aid=0003242839|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \uc138\ube10\ud2f4 \uce21 \"\ud638\uc2dcX\uc2b9\uad00X\ub3c4\uacb8, \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \uc720\ub2db 3\uc6d4 \uacf5\uac1c\"|publisher=\uc11c\uacbd\uc2a4\ud0c0|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Seventeen discography}}\n* ''[[Love & Letter]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Teen, Age]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[An Ode]]'' (2019)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Network\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n| ''Big Debut Plan''<ref name=\"naver1\"/>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016\n| ''Seventeen's One Fine Day''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mbcplus.com/seventeenday|title=Seventeenday|accessdate=2017-02-26|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422114328/http://www.mbcplus.com/seventeenday|archivedate=April 22, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2017\n| ''Seventeen's One Fine Day in Japan''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000241341|title=\uc138\ube10\ud2f4, \uc0ac\uc0c1 \ucd5c\ucd08 '\uc5b4\ub290 \uba4b\uc9c4 \ub0a0' \uc7ac\ucd9c\uc5f0...\uc77c\ubcf8\uc11c \uc0dd\uc874\ub825 \uac80\uc99d|last=|first=|date=2016-12-26|website=Naver News|publisher